  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: From Adam to Noah\u2019s Sons"
      title: "From Adam to Noah\u2019s Sons"
      number: 1
      content: '  The descendants of Adam were Seth, Enosh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Descendants of Japheth'
      title: Descendants of Japheth
      number: 4
      content: 'and Noah.The sons of Noah were[[COMMENT(0)]] Shem, Ham, and Japheth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: As in Greek version (see also Gen 5:3-32); Hebrew lacks <b>The sons
          of Noah were.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The descendants of Japheth were Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal,
        Meshech, and Tiras.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The descendants of Gomer were Ashkenaz, Riphath,[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        Togarmah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version (see also Gen 10:3);
          most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Diphath.</b>
    - name: '7: Descendants of Ham'
      title: Descendants of Ham
      number: 7
      content: 'The descendants of Javan were Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rodanim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The descendants of Ham were Cush, Mizraim,[[COMMENT(0)]] Put, and
        Canaan.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Or <b>Egypt; </b>also in 1:11.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The descendants of Cush were Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca.
        The descendants of Raamah were Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Cush was also the ancestor of Nimrod, who was the first heroic warrior
        on earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mizraim was the ancestor of the Ludites, Anamites, Lehabites, Naphtuhites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Pathrusites, Casluhites, and the Caphtorites, from whom the Philistines
        came.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Casluhites, from whom the Philistines came, Caphtorites.
          </b>See Jer 47:4; Amos 9:7.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Canaan\u2019s oldest son was Sidon, the ancestor of the Sidonians.
        Canaan was also the ancestor of the Hittites,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>ancestor of Heth.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jebusites, Amorites, Girgashites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hivites, Arkites, Sinites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Descendants of Shem'
      title: Descendants of Shem
      number: 16
      content: 'Arvadites, Zemarites, and Hamathites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The descendants of Shem were Elam, Asshur, Arphaxad, Lud, and Aram.The
        descendants of Aram were[[COMMENT(0)]] Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:17a '
        content: As in one Hebrew manuscript and some Greek manuscripts (see also
          Gen 10:23); most Hebrew manuscripts lack <b>The descendants of Aram were.</b>
      - number: '1:17b '
        content: As in parallel text at Gen 10:23; Hebrew reads <b>and Meshech.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Arphaxad was the father of Shelah.Shelah was the father of Eber.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Eber had two sons. The first was named Peleg (which means \u201Cdivision\u201D),
        for during his lifetime the people of the world were divided into different
        language groups. His brother\u2019s name was Joktan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Joktan was the ancestor of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Obal,[[COMMENT(0)]] Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:22 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac version (see also Gen 10:28);
          most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Ebal.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were descendants of Joktan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So this is the family line descended from Shem: Arphaxad, Shelah,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:24 '
        content: Some Greek manuscripts read <b>Arphaxad, Cainan, Shelah. </b>See
          notes on Gen 10:24; 11:12-13.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Eber, Peleg, Reu, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Serug, Nahor, Terah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Descendants of Abraham'
      title: Descendants of Abraham
      number: 27
      content: 'and Abram, later known as Abraham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Abraham were Isaac and Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These are their genealogical records:The sons of Ishmael were Nebaioth
        (the oldest), Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These were the sons of Ishmael.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The sons of Keturah, Abraham\u2019s concubine, were Zimran, Jokshan,
        Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah.The sons of Jokshan were Sheba and Dedan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Descendants of Isaac'
      title: Descendants of Isaac
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah.All
        these were descendants of Abraham through his concubine Keturah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Descendants of Esau'
      title: Descendants of Esau
      number: 34
      content: 'Abraham was the father of Isaac. The sons of Isaac were Esau and
        Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:34 '
        content: <b>Israel </b>is the name that God gave to Jacob.
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Esau were Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The descendants of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Gatam, Kenaz, and Amalek, who was born to Timna.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:36a '
        content: As in many Hebrew manuscripts and a few Greek manuscripts (see also
          Gen 36:11); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Zephi.</b>
      - number: '1:36b '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also Gen 36:12); Hebrew reads
          <b>Kenaz, Timna, and Amalek.</b>
    - name: '37: Original Peoples of Edom'
      title: Original Peoples of Edom
      number: 37
      content: 'The descendants of Reuel were Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The descendants of Seir were Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon,
        Ezer, and Dishan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "The descendants of Lotan were Hori and Hemam.[[COMMENT(0)]] Lotan\u2019s
        sister was named Timna.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:39 '
        content: As in parallel text at Gen 36:22; Hebrew reads <b>and Homam.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The descendants of Shobal were Alvan,[[COMMENT(0)]] Manahath, Ebal,
        Shepho,[[COMMENT(1)]] and Onam.The descendants of Zibeon were Aiah and Anah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:40a '
        content: As in many Hebrew manuscripts and a few Greek manuscripts (see also
          Gen 36:23); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Alian.</b>
      - number: '1:40b '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts (see also Gen 36:23); most Hebrew
          manuscripts read <b>Shephi.</b>
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The son of Anah was Dishon.The descendants of Dishon were Hemdan,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Eshban, Ithran, and Keran.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:41 '
        content: As in many Hebrew manuscripts and some Greek manuscripts (see also
          Gen 36:26); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Hamran.</b>
    - name: '42: Rulers of Edom'
      title: Rulers of Edom
      number: 42
      content: 'The descendants of Ezer were Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.[[COMMENT(0)]]The
        descendants of Dishan[[COMMENT(1)]] were Uz and Aran.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:42a '
        content: As in many Hebrew and Greek manuscripts (see also Gen 36:27); most
          Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Jaakan.</b>
      - number: '1:42b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Dishon; </b>compare 1:38 and parallel text at Gen 36:28.
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'These are the kings who ruled in the land of Edom before any king
        ruled over the Israelites[[COMMENT(0)]]:Bela son of Beor, who ruled from
        his city of Dinhabah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:43 '
        content: Or <b>before an Israelite king ruled over them.</b>
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah became king in his
        place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites became king
        in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad became king in his place and
        ruled from the city of Avith. He was the one who destroyed the Midianite
        army in the land of Moab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When Hadad died, Samlah from the city of Masrekah became king in
        his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When Samlah died, Shaul from the city of Rehoboth-on-the-River became
        king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'When Shaul died, Baal-hanan son of Acbor became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'When Baal-hanan died, Hadad became king in his place and ruled from
        the city of Pau.[[COMMENT(0)]] His wife was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred
        and granddaughter of Me-zahab. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:50 '
        content: As in many Hebrew manuscripts, some Greek manuscripts, Syriac version,
          and Latin Vulgate (see also Gen 36:39); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Pai.</b>
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Then Hadad died.The clan leaders of Edom were Timna, Alvah,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Jetheth, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:51 '
        content: As in an alternate reading of the Masoretic Text (see also Gen 36:40);
          the other alternate reads <b>Aliah.</b>
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: Magdiel, and Iram. These are the clan leaders of Edom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Israel'
      title: Descendants of Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  The sons of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] were Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah,
        Issachar, Zebulun, '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: <b>Israel </b>is the name that God gave to Jacob.
    - name: '2: Descendants of Judah'
      title: Descendants of Judah
      number: 2
      content: 'Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Judah had three sons from Bathshua, a Canaanite woman. Their names
        were Er, Onan, and Shelah. But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw that the
        oldest son, Er, was a wicked man, so he killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Later Judah had twin sons from Tamar, his widowed daughter-in-law.
        Their names were Perez and Zerah. So Judah had five sons in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The sons of Zerah were Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Darda[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014five
        in all.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: As in many Hebrew manuscripts, some Greek manuscripts, and Syriac
          version (see also 1 Kgs 4:31); Hebrew reads <b>Dara.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The son of Carmi (a descendant of Zimri) was Achan,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who brought disaster on Israel by taking plunder that had been set apart
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(1)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '2:7a '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Achar; </b>compare Josh 7:1. <b>Achar </b>means \u201Cdisaster.\u201D"
      - number: '2:7b '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - name: "8: From Judah\u2019s Grandson Hezron to David"
      title: "From Judah\u2019s Grandson Hezron to David"
      number: 8
      content: 'The son of Ethan was Azariah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Hezron were Jerahmeel, Ram, and Caleb.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Kelubai, </b>a variant spelling of Caleb; compare 2:18.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ram was the father of Amminadab.Amminadab was the father of Nahshon,
        a leader of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nahshon was the father of Salmon.[[COMMENT(0)]]Salmon was the father
        of Boaz.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: As in Greek version (see also Ruth 4:20); Hebrew reads <b>Salma.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Boaz was the father of Obed.Obed was the father of Jesse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesse\u2019s first son was Eliab, his second was Abinadab, his third
        was Shimea, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'his fourth was Nethanel, his fifth was Raddai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'his sixth was Ozem, and his seventh was David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their sisters were named Zeruiah and Abigail. Zeruiah had three sons
        named Abishai, Joab, and Asahel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Other Descendants of Hezron'
      title: Other Descendants of Hezron
      number: 17
      content: 'Abigail married a man named Jether, an Ishmaelite, and they had a
        son named Amasa.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Hezron\u2019s son Caleb had sons from his wife Azubah and from Jerioth.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Her sons were named Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: Or <b>Caleb had a daughter named Jerioth from his wife, Azubah.
          </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'After Azubah died, Caleb married Ephrathah,[[COMMENT(0)]] and they
        had a son named Hur. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephrath, </b>a variant spelling of Ephrathah; compare
          2:50 and 4:4.
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Hur was the father of Uri. Uri was the father of Bezalel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When Hezron was sixty years old, he married Gilead\u2019s sister,
        the daughter of Makir. They had a son named Segub. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Segub was the father of Jair, who ruled twenty-three towns in the
        land of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '(But Geshur and Aram captured the Towns of Jair[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        also took Kenath and its sixty surrounding villages.) All these were descendants
        of Makir, the father of Gilead.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: Or <b>captured Havvoth-jair.</b>
    - name: "24: Descendants of Hezron\u2019s Son Jerahmeel"
      title: "Descendants of Hezron\u2019s Son Jerahmeel"
      number: 24
      content: 'Soon after Hezron died in the town of Caleb-ephrathah, his wife Abijah
        gave birth to a son named Ashhur (the father of[[COMMENT(0)]] Tekoa).  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:24 '
        content: Or <b>the founder of; </b>also in 2:42, 45, 49.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Jerahmeel, the oldest son of Hezron, were Ram (the firstborn),
        Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Jerahmeel had a second wife named Atarah. She was the mother of Onam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Ram, the oldest son of Jerahmeel, were Maaz, Jamin, and
        Eker.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Onam were Shammai and Jada.The sons of Shammai were Nadab
        and Abishur.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The sons of Abishur and his wife Abihail were Ahban and Molid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The sons of Nadab were Seled and Appaim. Seled died without children, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'but Appaim had a son named Ishi. The son of Ishi was Sheshan. Sheshan
        had a descendant named Ahlai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The sons of Jada, Shammai\u2019s brother, were Jether and Jonathan.
        Jether died without children, "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'but Jonathan had two sons named Peleth and Zaza.These were all descendants
        of Jerahmeel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Sheshan had no sons, though he did have daughters. He also had an
        Egyptian servant named Jarha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Sheshan gave one of his daughters to be the wife of Jarha, and they
        had a son named Attai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Attai was the father of Nathan.Nathan was the father of Zabad.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zabad was the father of Ephlal.Ephlal was the father of Obed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Obed was the father of Jehu.Jehu was the father of Azariah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Azariah was the father of Helez.Helez was the father of Eleasah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Eleasah was the father of Sismai.Sismai was the father of Shallum.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "41: Descendants of Hezron\u2019s Son Caleb"
      title: "Descendants of Hezron\u2019s Son Caleb"
      number: 41
      content: 'Shallum was the father of Jekamiah.Jekamiah was the father of Elishama.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "The descendants of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel, included Mesha
        (the firstborn), who became the father of Ziph. Caleb\u2019s descendants
        also included the sons of Mareshah, the father of Hebron.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:42 '
        content: Or <b>who founded Hebron. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The sons of Hebron were Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Shema was the father of Raham. Raham was the father of Jorkeam. Rekem
        was the father of Shammai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The son of Shammai was Maon. Maon was the father of Beth-zur.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Caleb\u2019s concubine Ephah gave birth to Haran, Moza, and Gazez.
        Haran was the father of Gazez.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The sons of Jahdai were Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and
        Shaaph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Another of Caleb\u2019s concubines, Maacah, gave birth to Sheber
        and Tirhanah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'She also gave birth to Shaaph (the father of Madmannah) and Sheva
        (the father of Macbenah and Gibea). Caleb also had a daughter named Acsah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "50: Descendants of Caleb\u2019s Son Hur"
      title: "Descendants of Caleb\u2019s Son Hur"
      number: 50
      content: "These were all descendants of Caleb.The sons of Hur, the oldest son
        of Caleb\u2019s wife Ephrathah, were Shobal (the founder of Kiriath-jearim), "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Salma (the founder of Bethlehem), and Hareph (the founder of Beth-gader).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'The descendants of Shobal (the founder of Kiriath-jearim) were Haroeh,
        half the Manahathites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "and the families of Kiriath-jearim\u2014the Ithrites, Puthites, Shumathites,
        and Mishraites, from whom came the people of Zorah and Eshtaol.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The descendants of Salma were the people of Bethlehem, the Netophathites,
        Atroth-beth-joab, the other half of the Manahathites, the Zorites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "and the families of scribes living at Jabez\u2014the Tirathites,
        Shimeathites, and Sucathites. All these were Kenites who descended from Hammath,
        the father of the family of Recab.[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '2:55 '
        content: Or <b>the founder of Beth-recab.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of David'
      title: Descendants of David
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the sons of David who were born in Hebron:The oldest
        was Amnon, whose mother was Ahinoam from Jezreel.The second was Daniel, whose
        mother was Abigail from Carmel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The third was Absalom, whose mother was Maacah, the daughter of Talmai,
        king of Geshur.The fourth was Adonijah, whose mother was Haggith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The fifth was Shephatiah, whose mother was Abital.The sixth was Ithream,
        whose mother was Eglah, David\u2019s wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These six sons were born to David in Hebron, where he reigned seven
        and a half years.Then David reigned another thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons born to David in Jerusalem included Shammua,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Shobab, Nathan, and Solomon. Their mother was Bathsheba,[[COMMENT(1)]] the
        daughter of Ammiel. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:5a '
        content: As in Syriac version (see also 14:4; 2 Sam 5:14); Hebrew reads <b>Shimea.</b>
      - number: '3:5b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Bathshua, </b>a variant spelling of Bathsheba.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'David also had nine other sons: Ibhar, Elishua,[[COMMENT(0)]] Elpelet,[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6a '
        content: As in some Hebrew and Greek manuscripts (see also 14:5-7 and 2 Sam
          5:15); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Elishama.</b>
      - number: '3:6b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Eliphelet; </b>compare parallel text at 14:5-7.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Descendants of Solomon'
      title: Descendants of Solomon
      number: 9
      content: 'These were the sons of David, not including his sons born to his
        concubines. Their sister was named Tamar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The descendants of Solomon were Rehoboam, Abijah, Asa, Jehoshaphat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Jehoram,[[COMMENT(0)]] Ahaziah, Joash, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Joram, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoram.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Amaziah, Uzziah,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jotham, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Azariah, </b>a variant spelling of Uzziah.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ahaz, Hezekiah, Manasseh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Amon, and Josiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Josiah were Johanan (the oldest), Jehoiakim (the second),
        Zedekiah (the third), and Jehoahaz[[COMMENT(0)]] (the fourth).  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shallum, </b>another name for Jehoahaz.
    - name: '16: Descendants of Jehoiachin'
      title: Descendants of Jehoiachin
      number: 16
      content: 'The successors of Jehoiakim were his son Jehoiachin and his brother
        Zedekiah.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>The sons of Jehoiakim were his son Jeconiah </b>[a variant
          spelling of Jehoiachin] <b>and his son Zedekiah.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Jehoiachin,[[COMMENT(0)]] who was taken prisoner by the
        Babylonians, were Shealtiel, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeconiah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Malkiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Pedaiah were Zerubbabel and Shimei.The sons of Zerubbabel
        were Meshullam and Hananiah. (Their sister was Shelomith.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'His five other sons were Hashubah, Ohel, Berekiah, Hasadiah, and
        Jushab-hesed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The sons of Hananiah were Pelatiah and Jeshaiah. Jeshaiah\u2019s
        son was Rephaiah. Rephaiah\u2019s son was Arnan. Arnan\u2019s son was Obadiah.
        Obadiah\u2019s son was Shecaniah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The descendants of Shecaniah were Shemaiah and his sons, Hattush,
        Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat\u2014six in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Neariah were Elioenai, Hizkiah, and Azrikam\u2014three
        in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The sons of Elioenai were Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan,
        Delaiah, and Anani\u2014seven in all."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Other Descendants of Judah'
      title: Other Descendants of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The descendants of Judah were Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Shobal\u2019s son Reaiah was the father of Jahath. Jahath was the
        father of Ahumai and Lahad. These were the families of the Zorathites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The descendants of[[COMMENT(0)]] Etam were Jezreel, Ishma, Idbash,
        their sister Hazzelelponi, '
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>father of. </b>The meaning
          of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Penuel (the father of[[COMMENT(0)]] Gedor), and Ezer (the father
        of Hushah). These were the descendants of Hur (the firstborn of Ephrathah),
        the ancestor of Bethlehem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Or <b>the founder of; </b>also in 4:5, 12, 14, 17, 18, and perhaps
          other instances where the text reads <b>the father of.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ashhur (the father of Tekoa) had two wives, named Helah and Naarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Naarah gave birth to Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Helah gave birth to Zereth, Izhar,[[COMMENT(0)]] Ethnan, '
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: As in an alternate reading in the Masoretic Text (see also Latin
          Vulgate); the other alternate and the Greek version read <b>Zohar.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Koz, who became the ancestor of Anub, Zobebah, and all the families
        of Aharhel son of Harum.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'There was a man named Jabez who was more honorable than any of his
        brothers. His mother named him Jabez[[COMMENT(0)]] because his birth had
        been so painful. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: "<b>Jabez </b>sounds like a Hebrew word meaning \u201Cdistress\u201D
          or \u201Cpain.\u201D"
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He was the one who prayed to the God of Israel, \u201COh, that you
        would bless me and expand my territory! Please be with me in all that I do,
        and keep me from all trouble and pain!\u201D And God granted him his request.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Kelub (the brother of Shuhah) was the father of Mehir. Mehir was
        the father of Eshton. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Eshton was the father of Beth-rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah. Tehinnah
        was the father of Ir-nahash. These were the descendants of Recah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The sons of Kenaz were Othniel and Seraiah. Othniel\u2019s sons were
        Hathath and Meonothai.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts and Latin Vulgate; Hebrew lacks <b>and
          Meonothai.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Meonothai was the father of Ophrah. Seraiah was the father of Joab,
        the founder of the Valley of Craftsmen,[[COMMENT(0)]] so called because they
        were craftsmen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:14 '
        content: Or <b>Joab, the father of Ge-harashim.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Caleb son of Jephunneh were Iru, Elah, and Naam. The
        son of Elah was Kenaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Jehallelel were Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The sons of Ezrah were Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. One of Mered\u2019s
        wives became[[COMMENT(0)]] the mother of Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah (the
        father of Eshtemoa). "
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: "Or <b>Jether\u2019s wife became; </b>Hebrew reads <b>She became.</b>"
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He married a woman from Judah, who became the mother of Jered (the
        father of Gedor), Heber (the father of Soco), and Jekuthiel (the father of
        Zanoah). Mered also married Bithia, a daughter of Pharaoh, and she bore him
        children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Hodiah\u2019s wife was the sister of Naham. One of her sons was the
        father of Keilah the Garmite, and another was the father of Eshtemoa the
        Maacathite.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Descendants of Judah\u2019s Son Shelah"
      title: "Descendants of Judah\u2019s Son Shelah"
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Shimon were Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-hanan, and Tilon.The descendants
        of Ishi were Zoheth and Ben-zoheth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Shelah was one of Judah\u2019s sons. The descendants of Shelah were
        Er (the father of Lecah); Laadah (the father of Mareshah); the families of
        linen workers at Beth-ashbea; "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Jokim; the men of Cozeba; and Joash and Saraph, who ruled over Moab
        and Jashubi-lehem. These names all come from ancient records. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Descendants of Simeon'
      title: Descendants of Simeon
      number: 23
      content: 'They were the pottery makers who lived in Netaim and Gederah. They
        lived there and worked for the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Simeon were Jemuel,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jamin, Jarib, Zohar,[[COMMENT(1)]]
        and Shaul.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:24a '
        content: As in Syriac version (see also Gen 46:10; Exod 6:15); Hebrew reads
          <b>Nemuel.</b>
      - number: '4:24b '
        content: As in parallel texts at Gen 46:10 and Exod 6:15; Hebrew reads <b>Zerah.</b>
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The descendants of Shaul were Shallum, Mibsam, and Mishma.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The descendants of Mishma were Hammuel, Zaccur, and Shimei.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters, but none of his brothers
        had large families. So Simeon\u2019s tribe never grew as large as the tribe
        of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They lived in Beersheba, Moladah, Hazar-shual, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susim, Beth-biri, and Shaaraim. These towns
        were under their control until the time of King David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Their descendants also lived in Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Token, and Ashan\u2014five
        towns "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and their surrounding villages as far away as Baalath.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        This was their territory, and these names are listed in their genealogical
        records.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:33 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also Josh 19:8); Hebrew reads
          <b>Baal.</b>
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Other descendants of Simeon included Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah son
        of Amaziah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Joel, Jehu son of Joshibiah, son of Seraiah, son of Asiel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and Ziza son of Shiphi, son of Allon, son of Jedaiah, son of Shimri,
        son of Shemaiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "These were the names of some of the leaders of Simeon\u2019s wealthy
        clans. Their families grew, "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and they traveled to the region of Gerar,[[COMMENT(0)]] in the east
        part of the valley, seeking pastureland for their flocks. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:39 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>Gedor.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "They found lush pastures there, and the land was spacious, quiet,
        and peaceful.Some of Ham\u2019s descendants had been living in that region. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: But during the reign of King Hezekiah of Judah, these leaders of Simeon
        invaded the region and completely destroyed[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> the
        homes of the descendants of Ham and of the Meunites. No trace of them remains
        today. They killed everyone who lived there and took the land for themselves,
        because they wanted its good pastureland for their flocks. </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '4:41 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Five hundred of these invaders from the tribe of Simeon went to Mount
        Seir, led by Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel\u2014all sons of Ishi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: They destroyed the few Amalekites who had survived, and they have
        lived there ever since.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Reuben'
      title: Descendants of Reuben
      number: 1
      content: "  The oldest son of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] was Reuben. But since he
        dishonored his father by sleeping with one of his father\u2019s concubines,
        his birthright was given to the sons of his brother Joseph. For this reason,
        Reuben is not listed in the genealogical records as the firstborn son. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: <b>Israel </b>is the name that God gave to Jacob.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The descendants of Judah became the most powerful tribe and provided
        a ruler for the nation,[[COMMENT(0)]] but the birthright belonged to Joseph.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: Or <b>and from Judah came a prince.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Reuben, the oldest son of Israel, were Hanoch, Pallu,
        Hezron, and Carmi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The descendants of Joel were Shemaiah, Gog, Shimei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Micah, Reaiah, Baal, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Beerah. Beerah was the leader of the Reubenites when they were
        taken into captivity by King Tiglath-pileser[[COMMENT(0)]] of Assyria.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tilgath-pilneser, </b>a variant spelling of Tiglath-pileser;
          also in 5:26.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Beerah\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] relatives are listed in their genealogical
        records by their clans: Jeiel (the leader), Zechariah, "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>His.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Bela son of Azaz, son of Shema, son of Joel.The Reubenites lived
        in the area that stretches from Aroer to Nebo and Baal-meon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And since they had so many livestock in the land of Gilead, they
        spread east toward the edge of the desert that stretches to the Euphrates
        River.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Descendants of Gad'
      title: Descendants of Gad
      number: 10
      content: 'During the reign of Saul, the Reubenites defeated the Hagrites in
        battle. Then they moved into the Hagrite settlements all along the eastern
        edge of Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Next to the Reubenites, the descendants of Gad lived in the land
        of Bashan as far east as Salecah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Joel was the leader in the land of Bashan, and Shapham was second-in-command,
        followed by Janai and Shaphat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Their relatives, the leaders of seven other clans, were Michael,
        Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia, and Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These were all descendants of Abihail son of Huri, son of Jaroah,
        son of Gilead, son of Michael, son of Jeshishai, son of Jahdo, son of Buz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ahi son of Abdiel, son of Guni, was the leader of their clans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Gadites lived in the land of Gilead, in Bashan and its villages,
        and throughout all the pasturelands of Sharon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Tribes East of the Jordan'
      title: The Tribes East of the Jordan
      number: 17
      content: 'All of these were listed in the genealogical records during the days
        of King Jotham of Judah and King Jeroboam of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There were 44,760 capable warriors in the armies of Reuben, Gad,
        and the half-tribe of Manasseh. They were all skilled in combat and armed
        with shields, swords, and bows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They waged war against the Hagrites, the Jeturites, the Naphishites,
        and the Nodabites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They cried out to God during the battle, and he answered their prayer
        because they trusted in him. So the Hagrites and all their allies were defeated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The plunder taken from the Hagrites included 50,000 camels, 250,000
        sheep and goats, 2,000 donkeys, and 100,000 captives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Many of the Hagrites were killed in the battle because God was fighting
        against them. The people of Reuben, Gad, and Manasseh lived in their land
        until they were taken into exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The half-tribe of Manasseh was very large and spread through the
        land from Bashan to Baal-hermon, Senir, and Mount Hermon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These were the leaders of their clans: Epher,[[COMMENT(0)]] Ishi,
        Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel. These men had a great reputation
        as mighty warriors and leaders of their clans.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:24 '
        content: As in Greek version and Latin Vulgate; Hebrew reads <b>and Epher.</b>
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But these tribes were unfaithful to the God of their ancestors. They
        worshiped the gods of the nations that God had destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So the God of Israel caused King Pul of Assyria (also known as Tiglath-pileser)
        to invade the land and take away the people of Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh as captives. The Assyrians exiled them to Halah, Habor, Hara,
        and the Gozan River, where they remain to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priestly Line'
      title: The Priestly Line
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]The sons of Levi were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: '  Verses 6:1-15 are numbered 5:27-41 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The descendants of Kohath included Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The children of Amram were Aaron, Moses, and Miriam.The sons of Aaron
        were Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eleazar was the father of Phinehas.Phinehas was the father of Abishua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abishua was the father of Bukki.Bukki was the father of Uzzi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Uzzi was the father of Zerahiah.Zerahiah was the father of Meraioth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meraioth was the father of Amariah.Amariah was the father of Ahitub.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ahitub was the father of Zadok.Zadok was the father of Ahimaaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ahimaaz was the father of Azariah.Azariah was the father of Johanan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Johanan was the father of Azariah, the high priest at the Temple[[COMMENT(0)]]
        built by Solomon in Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>the house.</b>  '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Azariah was the father of Amariah.Amariah was the father of Ahitub.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ahitub was the father of Zadok.Zadok was the father of Shallum.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum was the father of Hilkiah.Hilkiah was the father of Azariah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Azariah was the father of Seraiah.Seraiah was the father of Jehozadak, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Levite Clans'
      title: The Levite Clans
      number: 15
      content: 'who went into exile when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent the
        people of Judah and Jerusalem into captivity under Nebuchadnezzar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]The sons of Levi were Gershon,[[COMMENT(1)]] Kohath,
        and Merari.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:16a '
        content: '  Verses 6:16-81 are numbered 6:1-66 in Hebrew text.  '
      - number: '6:16b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Gershom, </b>a variant spelling of Gershon (see 6:1);
          also in 6:17, 20, 43, 62, 71.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The descendants of Gershon included Libni and Shimei.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The descendants of Kohath included Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The descendants of Merari included Mahli and Mushi.The following
        were the Levite clans, listed according to their ancestral descent:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The descendants of Gershon included Libni, Jahath, Zimmah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Joah, Iddo, Zerah, and Jeatherai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The descendants of Kohath included Amminadab, Korah, Assir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Elkanah, Abiasaph,[[COMMENT(0)]] Assir, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ebiasaph, </b>a variant spelling of Abiasaph (also in
          6:37); compare parallel text at Exod 6:24.
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Tahath, Uriel, Uzziah, and Shaul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The descendants of Elkanah included Amasai, Ahimoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Elkanah, Zophai, Nahath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Eliab, Jeroham, Elkanah, and Samuel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:27 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also 6:33-34); Hebrew lacks <b>and
          Samuel.</b>
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Samuel were Joel[[COMMENT(0)]] (the older) and Abijah
        (the second).  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:28 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts and the Syriac version (see also 6:33
          and 1 Sam 8:2); Hebrew lacks <b>Joel.</b>
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The descendants of Merari included Mahli, Libni, Shimei, Uzzah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Temple Musicians'
      title: The Temple Musicians
      number: 30
      content: 'Shimea, Haggiah, and Asaiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'David assigned the following men to lead the music at the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> after the Ark was placed there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They ministered with music at the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]] until
        Solomon built the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in Jerusalem.
        They carried out their work, following all the regulations handed down to
        them. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:32 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Tabernacle, the Tent of Meeting.</b>
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'These are the men who served, along with their sons:Heman the musician
        was from the clan of Kohath. His genealogy was traced back through Joel,
        Samuel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Elkanah, Jeroham, Eliel, Toah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Zuph, Elkanah, Mahath, Amasai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Elkanah, Joel, Azariah, Zephaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Tahath, Assir, Abiasaph, Korah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Izhar, Kohath, Levi, and Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:38 '
        content: <b>Israel </b>is the name that God gave to Jacob.
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Heman\u2019s first assistant was Asaph from the clan of Gershon.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Asaph\u2019s genealogy was traced back through Berekiah, Shimea, "
      comments:
      - number: '6:39 '
        content: Hebrew lacks <b>from the clan of Gershon; </b>see 6:43.
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Michael, Baaseiah, Malkijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Ethni, Zerah, Adaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Ethan, Zimmah, Shimei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Jahath, Gershon, and Levi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Heman\u2019s second assistant was Ethan from the clan of Merari.
        Ethan\u2019s genealogy was traced back through Kishi, Abdi, Malluch, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Hashabiah, Amaziah, Hilkiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Amzi, Bani, Shemer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Mahli, Mushi, Merari, and Levi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "48: Aaron\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Aaron\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 48
      content: 'Their fellow Levites were appointed to various other tasks in the
        Tabernacle, the house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Only Aaron and his descendants served as priests. They presented
        the offerings on the altar of burnt offering and the altar of incense, and
        they performed all the other duties related to the Most Holy Place. They
        made atonement for Israel by doing everything that Moses, the servant of
        God, had commanded them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'The descendants of Aaron were Eleazar, Phinehas, Abishua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Bukki, Uzzi, Zerahiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Meraioth, Amariah, Ahitub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: Territory for the Levites'
      title: Territory for the Levites
      number: 53
      content: 'Zadok, and Ahimaaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'This is a record of the towns and territory assigned by means of
        sacred lots to the descendants of Aaron, who were from the clan of Kohath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'This territory included Hebron and its surrounding pasturelands in
        Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'but the fields and outlying areas belonging to the city were given
        to Caleb son of Jephunneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'So the descendants of Aaron were given the following towns, each
        with its pasturelands: Hebron (a city of refuge),[[COMMENT(0)]] Libnah, Jattir,
        Eshtemoa, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:57 '
        content: 'As in parallel text at Josh 21:13; Hebrew reads <b>were given the
          cities of refuge: Hebron, and the following towns, each with its pasturelands.</b>'
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Holon,[[COMMENT(0)]] Debir, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:58 '
        content: As in parallel text at Josh 21:15; Masoretic Text reads <b>Hilez;
          </b>other manuscripts read <b>Hilen.</b>
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Ain,[[COMMENT(0)]] Juttah,[[COMMENT(1)]] and Beth-shemesh. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:59a '
        content: As in parallel text at Josh 21:16; Hebrew reads <b>Ashan.</b>
      - number: '6:59b '
        content: As in Syriac version (see also Josh 21:16); Hebrew lacks <b>Juttah.</b>
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'And from the territory of Benjamin they were given Gibeon,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Geba, Alemeth, and Anathoth, each with its pasturelands. So thirteen towns
        were given to the descendants of Aaron. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:60 '
        content: As in parallel text at Josh 21:17; Hebrew lacks <b>Gibeon.</b>
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'The remaining descendants of Kohath received ten towns from the territory
        of the half-tribe of Manasseh by means of sacred lots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'The descendants of Gershon received by sacred lots thirteen towns
        from the territories of Issachar, Asher, Naphtali, and from the Bashan area
        of Manasseh, east of the Jordan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'The descendants of Merari received by sacred lots twelve towns from
        the territories of Reuben, Gad, and Zebulun.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'So the people of Israel assigned all these towns and pasturelands
        to the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'The towns in the territories of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin, mentioned
        above, were assigned to them by means of sacred lots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'The descendants of Kohath were given the following towns from the
        territory of Ephraim, each with its pasturelands: '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'Shechem (a city of refuge in the hill country of Ephraim),[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Gezer, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:66-67 '
        content: 'As in parallel text at Josh 21:21; Hebrew text reads <b>were given
          the cities of refuge: Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and the following
          towns, each with its pasturelands.</b>'
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Jokmeam, Beth-horon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'Aijalon, and Gath-rimmon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'The remaining descendants of Kohath were assigned the towns of Aner
        and Bileam from the territory of the half-tribe of Manasseh, each with its
        pasturelands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: 'The descendants of Gershon received the towns of Golan (in Bashan)
        and Ashtaroth from the territory of the half-tribe of Manasseh, each with
        its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: 'From the territory of Issachar, they were given Kedesh, Daberath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: 'Ramoth, and Anem, each with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '74: '
      title: 
      number: 74
      content: 'From the territory of Asher, they received Mashal, Abdon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '75: '
      title: 
      number: 75
      content: 'Hukok, and Rehob, each with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '76: '
      title: 
      number: 76
      content: 'From the territory of Naphtali, they were given Kedesh in Galilee,
        Hammon, and Kiriathaim, each with its pasturelands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '77: '
      title: 
      number: 77
      content: 'The remaining descendants of Merari received the towns of Jokneam,
        Kartah,[[COMMENT(0)]] Rimmon,[[COMMENT(1)]] and Tabor from the territory
        of Zebulun, each with its pasturelands. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:77a '
        content: As in Greek version (see also Josh 21:34); Hebrew lacks <b>Jokneam,
          Kartah.</b>
      - number: '6:77b '
        content: As in Greek version (see also Josh 19:13); Hebrew reads <b>Rimmono.</b>
    - name: '78: '
      title: 
      number: 78
      content: 'From the territory of Reuben, east of the Jordan River opposite Jericho,
        they received Bezer (a desert town), Jahaz,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:78 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jahzah, </b>a variant spelling of Jahaz.
    - name: '79: '
      title: 
      number: 79
      content: 'Kedemoth, and Mephaath, each with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '80: '
      title: 
      number: 80
      content: 'And from the territory of Gad, they received Ramoth in Gilead, Mahanaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '81: '
      title: 
      number: 81
      content: Heshbon, and Jazer, each with its pasturelands.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Issachar'
      title: Descendants of Issachar
      number: 1
      content: '  The four sons of Issachar were Tola, Puah, Jashub, and Shimron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Tola were Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam, and
        Shemuel. Each of them was the leader of an ancestral clan. At the time of
        King David, the total number of mighty warriors listed in the records of
        these clans was 22,600.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The son of Uzzi was Izrahiah. The sons of Izrahiah were Michael,
        Obadiah, Joel, and Isshiah. These five became the leaders of clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'All of them had many wives and many sons, so the total number of
        men available for military service among their descendants was 36,000.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Descendants of Benjamin'
      title: Descendants of Benjamin
      number: 5
      content: 'The total number of mighty warriors from all the clans of the tribe
        of Issachar was 87,000. All of them were listed in their genealogical records.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Three of Benjamin\u2019s sons were Bela, Beker, and Jediael.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The five sons of Bela were Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri.
        Each of them was the leader of an ancestral clan. The total number of mighty
        warriors from these clans was 22,034, as listed in their genealogical records.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Beker were Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth,
        Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Each of them was the leader of an ancestral clan. The total number
        of mighty warriors and leaders from these clans was 20,200, as listed in
        their genealogical records.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The son of Jediael was Bilhan. The sons of Bilhan were Jeush, Benjamin,
        Ehud, Kenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Each of them was the leader of an ancestral clan. From these clans
        the total number of mighty warriors ready for war was 17,200.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Descendants of Naphtali'
      title: Descendants of Naphtali
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Ir were Shuppim and Huppim. Hushim was the son of Aher.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Descendants of Manasseh'
      title: Descendants of Manasseh
      number: 13
      content: "The sons of Naphtali were Jahzeel,[[COMMENT(0)]] Guni, Jezer, and
        Shillem.[[COMMENT(1)]] They were all descendants of Jacob\u2019s concubine
        Bilhah.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:13a '
        content: As in parallel text at Gen 46:24; Hebrew reads <b>Jahziel, </b>a
          variant spelling of Jahzeel.
      - number: '7:13b '
        content: As in some Hebrew and Greek manuscripts (see also Gen 46:24; Num
          26:49); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Shallum.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The descendants of Manasseh through his Aramean concubine included
        Asriel. She also bore Makir, the father of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Makir found wives for[[COMMENT(0)]] Huppim and Shuppim. Makir had
        a sister named Maacah. One of his descendants was Zelophehad, who had only
        daughters.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        content: Or <b>Makir took a wife from. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Makir\u2019s wife, Maacah, gave birth to a son whom she named Peresh.
        His brother\u2019s name was Sheresh. The sons of Peresh were Ulam and Rakem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The son of Ulam was Bedan. All these were considered Gileadites,
        descendants of Makir son of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Makir\u2019s sister Hammoleketh gave birth to Ishhod, Abiezer, and
        Mahlah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Descendants of Ephraim'
      title: Descendants of Ephraim
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The descendants of Ephraim were Shuthelah, Bered, Tahath, Eleadah,
        Tahath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zabad, Shuthelah, Ezer, and Elead. These two were killed trying to
        steal livestock from the local farmers near Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Their father, Ephraim, mourned for them a long time, and his relatives
        came to comfort him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Afterward Ephraim slept with his wife, and she became pregnant and
        gave birth to a son. Ephraim named him Beriah[[COMMENT(0)]] because of the
        tragedy his family had suffered. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: "<b>Beriah </b>sounds like a Hebrew term meaning \u201Ctragedy\u201D
          or \u201Cmisfortune.\u201D"
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He had a daughter named Sheerah. She built the towns of Lower and
        Upper Beth-horon and Uzzen-sheerah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The descendants of Ephraim included Rephah, Resheph, Telah, Tahan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ladan, Ammihud, Elishama, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Nun, and Joshua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The descendants of Ephraim lived in the territory that included Bethel
        and its surrounding towns to the south, Naaran to the east, Gezer and its
        villages to the west, and Shechem and its surrounding villages to the north
        as far as Ayyah and its towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Descendants of Asher'
      title: Descendants of Asher
      number: 29
      content: 'Along the border of Manasseh were the towns of Beth-shan,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Taanach, Megiddo, Dor, and their surrounding villages. The descendants of
        Joseph son of Israel[[COMMENT(1)]] lived in these towns.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:29a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Beth-shean, </b>a variant spelling of Beth-shan.
      - number: '7:29b '
        content: <b>Israel </b>is the name that God gave to Jacob.
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The sons of Asher were Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, and Beriah. They had
        a sister named Serah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sons of Beriah were Heber and Malkiel (the father of Birzaith).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The sons of Heber were Japhlet, Shomer, and Hotham. They had a sister
        named Shua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Japhlet were Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The sons of Shomer were Ahi,[[COMMENT(0)]] Rohgah, Hubbah, and Aram.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:34 '
        content: Or <b>The sons of Shomer, his brother, were.</b>
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of his brother Helem[[COMMENT(0)]] were Zophah, Imna, Shelesh,
        and Amal.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:35 '
        content: Possibly another name for <b>Hotham; </b>compare 7:32.
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Zophah were Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Beera.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:37 '
        content: Possibly another name for <b>Jether; </b>compare 7:38.
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The sons of Jether were Jephunneh, Pispah, and Ara.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The sons of Ulla were Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Each of these descendants of Asher was the head of an ancestral clan.
        They were all select men\u2014mighty warriors and outstanding leaders. The
        total number of men available for military service was 26,000, as listed
        in their genealogical records."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Benjamin'
      title: Descendants of Benjamin
      number: 1
      content: "  Benjamin\u2019s first son was Bela, the second was Ashbel, the
        third was Aharah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'the fourth was Nohah, and the fifth was Rapha.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Bela were Addar, Gera, Abihud,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:3 '
        content: Possibly <b>Gera the father of Ehud; </b>compare 8:6.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Ehud, leaders of the clans living at Geba, were exiled
        to Manahath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Ehud\u2019s sons were Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera. Gera, who led them
        into exile, was the father of Uzza and Ahihud.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: Or <b>Gera, that is Heglam, was the father of Uzza and Ahihud.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'After Shaharaim divorced his wives Hushim and Baara, he had children
        in the land of Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'His wife Hodesh gave birth to Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Jeuz, Sakia, and Mirmah. These sons all became the leaders of clans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Shaharaim\u2019s wife Hushim had already given birth to Abitub and
        Elpaal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Elpaal were Eber, Misham, Shemed (who built the towns
        of Ono and Lod and their nearby villages), '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Beriah, and Shema. They were the leaders of the clans living in Aijalon,
        and they drove out the inhabitants of Gath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Zebadiah, Arad, Eder, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were the sons of Beriah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jakim, Zicri, Zabdi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Ishpan, Eber, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Abdon, Zicri, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Iphdeiah, and Penuel were the sons of Shashak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zicri were the sons of Jeroham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Family of Saul'
      title: The Family of Saul
      number: 28
      content: 'These were the leaders of the ancestral clans; they were listed in
        their genealogical records, and they all lived in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jeiel[[COMMENT(0)]] (the father of[[COMMENT(1)]] Gibeon) lived in
        the town of Gibeon. His wife\u2019s name was Maacah, "
      comments:
      - number: '8:29a '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also 9:35); Hebrew lacks <b>Jeiel.</b>
      - number: '8:29b '
        content: Or <b>the founder of.</b>
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "and his oldest son was named Abdon. Jeiel\u2019s other sons were
        Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner,[[COMMENT(0)]] Nadab, "
      comments:
      - number: '8:30 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also 9:36); Hebrew lacks <b>Ner.</b>
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:31 '
        content: As in parallel text at 9:37; Hebrew reads <b>Zeker, </b>a variant
          spelling of Zechariah.
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and Mikloth, who was the father of Shimeam.[[COMMENT(0)]] All these
        families lived near each other in Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:32 '
        content: As in parallel text at 9:38; Hebrew reads <b>Shimeah, </b>a variant
          spelling of Shimeam.
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Ner was the father of Kish.Kish was the father of Saul.Saul was the
        father of Jonathan, Malkishua, Abinadab, and Esh-baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Jonathan was the father of Merib-baal.Merib-baal was the father of
        Micah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Micah was the father of Pithon, Melech, Tahrea,[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        Ahaz.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:35 '
        content: As in parallel text at 9:41; Hebrew reads <b>Tarea, </b>a variant
          spelling of Tahrea.
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Ahaz was the father of Jadah.[[COMMENT(0)]]Jadah was the father of
        Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri.Zimri was the father of Moza.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:36 '
        content: As in parallel text at 9:42; Hebrew reads <b>Jehoaddah, </b>a variant
          spelling of Jadah.
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Moza was the father of Binea.Binea was the father of Rephaiah.[[COMMENT(0)]]Rephaiah
        was the father of Eleasah.Eleasah was the father of Azel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:37 '
        content: As in parallel text at 9:43; Hebrew reads <b>Raphah, </b>a variant
          spelling of Rephaiah.
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Azel had six sons: Azrikam, Bokeru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and
        Hanan. These were the sons of Azel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Azel\u2019s brother Eshek had three sons: the first was Ulam, the
        second was Jeush, and the third was Eliphelet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Ulam\u2019s sons were all mighty warriors and expert archers. They
        had many sons and grandsons\u2014150 in all.All these were descendants of
        Benjamin."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Returning Exiles'
      title: The Returning Exiles
      number: 1
      content: '  So all Israel was listed in the genealogical records in The Book
        of the Kings of Israel.The people of Judah were exiled to Babylon because
        they were unfaithful to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The first of the exiles to return to their property in their former
        towns were priests, Levites, Temple servants, and other Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Some of the people from the tribes of Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and
        Manasseh came and settled in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'One family that returned was that of Uthai son of Ammihud, son of
        Omri, son of Imri, son of Bani, a descendant of Perez son of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Others returned from the Shilonite clan, including Asaiah (the oldest)
        and his sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'From the Zerahite clan, Jeuel returned with his relatives.In all,
        690 families from the tribe of Judah returned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'From the tribe of Benjamin came Sallu son of Meshullam, son of Hodaviah,
        son of Hassenuah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ibneiah son of Jeroham; Elah son of Uzzi, son of Micri; and Meshullam
        son of Shephatiah, son of Reuel, son of Ibnijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Returning Priests'
      title: The Returning Priests
      number: 9
      content: 'These men were all leaders of clans, and they were listed in their
        genealogical records. In all, 956 families from the tribe of Benjamin returned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Among the priests who returned were Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, Jakin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Azariah son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of Meraioth,
        son of Ahitub. Azariah was the chief officer of the house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Other returning priests were Adaiah son of Jeroham, son of Pashhur,
        son of Malkijah, and Maasai son of Adiel, son of Jahzerah, son of Meshullam,
        son of Meshillemith, son of Immer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Returning Levites'
      title: The Returning Levites
      number: 13
      content: 'In all, 1,760 priests returned. They were heads of clans and very
        able men. They were responsible for ministering at the house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Levites who returned were Shemaiah son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam,
        son of Hashabiah, a descendant of Merari; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bakbakkar; Heresh; Galal; Mattaniah son of Mica, son of Zicri, son
        of Asaph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Obadiah son of Shemaiah, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun; and Berekiah
        son of Asa, son of Elkanah, who lived in the area of Netophah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The gatekeepers who returned were Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman,
        and their relatives. Shallum was the chief gatekeeper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Prior to this time, they were responsible for the King\u2019s Gate
        on the east side. These men served as gatekeepers for the camps of the Levites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Shallum was the son of Kore, a descendant of Abiasaph,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from the clan of Korah. He and his relatives, the Korahites, were responsible
        for guarding the entrance to the sanctuary, just as their ancestors had guarded
        the Tabernacle in the camp of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ebiasaph, </b>a variant spelling of Abiasaph; compare
          Exod 6:24.
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Phinehas son of Eleazar had been in charge of the gatekeepers in
        earlier times, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had been with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And later Zechariah son of Meshelemiah was responsible for guarding
        the entrance to the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In all, there were 212 gatekeepers in those days, and they were listed
        according to the genealogies in their villages. David and Samuel the seer
        had appointed their ancestors because they were reliable men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These gatekeepers and their descendants, by their divisions, were
        responsible for guarding the entrance to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        when that house was a tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The gatekeepers were stationed on all four sides\u2014east, west,
        north, and south. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their relatives in the villages came regularly to share their duties
        for seven-day periods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The four chief gatekeepers, all Levites, were trusted officials,
        for they were responsible for the rooms and treasuries at the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They would spend the night around the house of God, since it was
        their duty to guard it and to open the gates every morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Some of the gatekeepers were assigned to care for the various articles
        used in worship. They checked them in and out to avoid any loss. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Others were responsible for the furnishings, the items in the sanctuary,
        and the supplies, such as choice flour, wine, olive oil, frankincense, and
        spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But it was the priests who blended the spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Mattithiah, a Levite and the oldest son of Shallum the Korahite,
        was entrusted with baking the bread used in the offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And some members of the clan of Kohath were in charge of preparing
        the bread to be set on the table each Sabbath day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The musicians, all prominent Levites, lived at the Temple. They were
        exempt from other responsibilities since they were on duty at all hours. '
      comments: []
    - name: "34: King Saul\u2019s Family Tree"
      title: "King Saul\u2019s Family Tree"
      number: 34
      content: 'All these men lived in Jerusalem. They were the heads of Levite families
        and were listed as prominent leaders in their genealogical records.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jeiel (the father of[[COMMENT(0)]] Gibeon) lived in the town of Gibeon.
        His wife\u2019s name was Maacah, "
      comments:
      - number: '9:35 '
        content: Or <b>the founder of.</b>
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "and his oldest son was named Abdon. Jeiel\u2019s other sons were
        Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab, "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Mikloth was the father of Shimeam. All these families lived near
        each other in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Ner was the father of Kish.Kish was the father of Saul.Saul was the
        father of Jonathan, Malkishua, Abinadab, and Esh-baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Jonathan was the father of Merib-baal.Merib-baal was the father of
        Micah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The sons of Micah were Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and Ahaz.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:41 '
        content: As in Syriac version and Latin Vulgate (see also 8:35); Hebrew lacks
          <b>and Ahaz.</b>
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Ahaz was the father of Jadah.[[COMMENT(0)]]Jadah was the father of
        Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri.Zimri was the father of Moza.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:42 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version (see also 8:36);
          Hebrew reads <b>Jarah.</b>
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Moza was the father of Binea.Binea\u2019s son was Rephaiah.Rephaiah\u2019s
        son was Eleasah.Eleasah\u2019s son was Azel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: Azel had six sons, whose names were Azrikam, Bokeru, Ishmael, Sheariah,
        Obadiah, and Hanan. These were the sons of Azel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of King Saul'
      title: The Death of King Saul
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Philistines attacked Israel, and the men of Israel fled
        before them. Many were slaughtered on the slopes of Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Philistines closed in on Saul and his sons, and they killed three
        of his sons\u2014Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malkishua. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The fighting grew very fierce around Saul, and the Philistine archers
        caught up with him and wounded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Saul groaned to his armor bearer, \u201CTake your sword and kill
        me before these pagan Philistines come to taunt and torture me.\u201DBut
        his armor bearer was afraid and would not do it. So Saul took his own sword
        and fell on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When his armor bearer realized that Saul was dead, he fell on his
        own sword and died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Saul and his three sons died there together, bringing his dynasty
        to an end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When all the Israelites in the Jezreel Valley saw that their army
        had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned their towns
        and fled. So the Philistines moved in and occupied their towns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The next day, when the Philistines went out to strip the dead, they
        found the bodies of Saul and his sons on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So they stripped off Saul\u2019s armor and cut off his head. Then
        they proclaimed the good news of Saul\u2019s death before their idols and
        to the people throughout the land of Philistia. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They placed his armor in the temple of their gods, and they fastened
        his head to the temple of Dagon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when everyone in Jabesh-gilead heard about everything the Philistines
        had done to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all their mighty warriors brought the bodies of Saul and his sons
        back to Jabesh. Then they buried their bones beneath the great tree at Jabesh,
        and they fasted for seven days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Saul died because he was unfaithful to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He failed to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s command, and he
        even consulted a medium "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: instead of asking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for guidance. So
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> killed him and turned the kingdom over to
        David son of Jesse.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Becomes King of All Israel'
      title: David Becomes King of All Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then all Israel gathered before David at Hebron and told him, \u201CWe
        are your own flesh and blood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In the past,[[COMMENT(0)]] even when Saul was king, you were the
        one who really led the forces of Israel. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God told you, \u2018You will be the shepherd of my people Israel. You
        will be the leader of my people Israel.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: Or <b>For some time.</b>
    - name: '3: David Captures Jerusalem'
      title: David Captures Jerusalem
      number: 3
      content: 'So there at Hebron, David made a covenant before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with all the elders of Israel. And they anointed him king of Israel, just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had promised through Samuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David and all Israel went to Jerusalem (or Jebus, as it used
        to be called), where the Jebusites, the original inhabitants of the land,
        were living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The people of Jebus taunted David, saying, \u201CYou\u2019ll never
        get in here!\u201D But David captured the fortress of Zion, which is now
        called the City of David.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "David had said to his troops, \u201CWhoever is first to attack the
        Jebusites will become the commander of my armies!\u201D And Joab, the son
        of David\u2019s sister Zeruiah, was first to attack, so he became the commander
        of David\u2019s armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'David made the fortress his home, and that is why it is called the
        City of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He extended the city from the supporting terraces[[COMMENT(0)]] to
        the surrounding area, while Joab rebuilt the rest of Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the millo. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: "9: David\u2019s Mightiest Warriors"
      title: "David\u2019s Mightiest Warriors"
      number: 9
      content: "And David became more and more powerful, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies was with him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "These are the leaders of David\u2019s mighty warriors. Together with
        all Israel, they decided to make David their king, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had promised concerning Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Here is the record of David\u2019s mightiest warriors: The first
        was Jashobeam the Hacmonite, who was leader of the Three\u2014the mightiest
        warriors among David\u2019s men.[[COMMENT(0)]] He once used his spear to
        kill 300 enemy warriors in a single battle.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:11 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts (see also 2 Sam 23:8); Hebrew reads
          <b>leader of the Thirty, </b>or <b>leader of the captains.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next in rank among the Three was Eleazar son of Dodai,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        a descendant of Ahoah. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:12 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:9 (see also 1 Chr 27:4); Hebrew
          reads <b>Dodo, </b>a variant spelling of Dodai.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He was with David when the Philistines gathered for battle at Pas-dammim
        and attacked the Israelites in a field full of barley. The Israelite army
        fled, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but Eleazar and David[[COMMENT(0)]] held their ground in the middle
        of the field and beat back the Philistines. So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        saved them by giving them a great victory.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>they.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Once when David was at the rock near the cave of Adullam, the Philistine
        army was camped in the valley of Rephaim. The Three (who were among the Thirty\u2014an
        elite group among David\u2019s fighting men) went down to meet him there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David was staying in the stronghold at the time, and a Philistine
        detachment had occupied the town of Bethlehem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "David remarked longingly to his men, \u201COh, how I would love some
        of that good water from the well by the gate in Bethlehem.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So the Three broke through the Philistine lines, drew some water
        from the well by the gate in Bethlehem, and brought it back to David. But
        David refused to drink it. Instead, he poured it out as an offering to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: David\u2019s Thirty Mighty Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Thirty Mighty Men"
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CGod forbid that I should drink this!\u201D he exclaimed. \u201CThis
        water is as precious as the blood of these men[[COMMENT(0)]] who risked their
        lives to bring it to me.\u201D So David did not drink it. These are examples
        of the exploits of the Three.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shall I drink the lifeblood of these men?</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Abishai, the brother of Joab, was the leader of the Thirty.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        He once used his spear to kill 300 enemy warriors in a single battle. It
        was by such feats that he became as famous as the Three. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:20 '
        content: As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads <b>the Three; </b>also in 11:21.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Abishai was the most famous of the Thirty and was their commander,
        though he was not one of the Three.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'There was also Benaiah son of Jehoiada, a valiant warrior from Kabzeel.
        He did many heroic deeds, which included killing two champions[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of Moab. Another time, on a snowy day, he chased a lion down into a pit and
        killed it. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:22 '
        content: Or <b>two sons of Ariel.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Once, armed only with a club, he killed an Egyptian warrior who was
        7-1/2 feet[[COMMENT(0)]] tall and who was armed with a spear as thick as
        a weaver\u2019s beam. Benaiah wrenched the spear from the Egyptian\u2019s
        hand and killed him with it. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>5 cubits </b>[2.3 meters].
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Deeds like these made Benaiah as famous as the three mightiest warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He was more honored than the other members of the Thirty, though
        he was not one of the Three. And David made him captain of his bodyguard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "David\u2019s mighty warriors also included:Asahel, Joab\u2019s brother;Elhanan
        son of Dodo from Bethlehem;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shammah from Harod;[[COMMENT(0)]]Helez from Pelon;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:27 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:25; Hebrew reads <b>Shammoth from
          Haror.</b>
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ira son of Ikkesh from Tekoa;Abiezer from Anathoth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Sibbecai from Hushah;Zalmon[[COMMENT(0)]] from Ahoah;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:29 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:28; Hebrew reads <b>Ilai.</b>
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Maharai from Netophah;Heled son of Baanah from Netophah;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ithai son of Ribai from Gibeah (in the land of Benjamin);Benaiah
        from Pirathon;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Hurai from near Nahale-gaash[[COMMENT(0)]];Abi-albon[[COMMENT(1)]]
        from Arabah;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:32a '
        content: Or <b>from the ravines of Gaash.</b>
      - number: '11:32b '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:31; Hebrew reads <b>Abiel.</b>
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Azmaveth from Bahurim[[COMMENT(0)]];Eliahba from Shaalbon;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:33 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:31; Hebrew reads <b>Baharum.</b>
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'the sons of Jashen[[COMMENT(0)]] from Gizon;Jonathan son of Shagee
        from Harar;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:34 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:32; Hebrew reads <b>sons of Hashem.</b>
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Ahiam son of Sharar[[COMMENT(0)]] from Harar;Eliphal son of Ur;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:35 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:33; Hebrew reads <b>son of Sacar.</b>
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Hepher from Mekerah;Ahijah from Pelon;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Hezro from Carmel;Paarai[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Ezbai;  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:37 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 23:35; Hebrew reads <b>Naarai.</b>
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joel, the brother of Nathan;Mibhar son of Hagri;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Zelek from Ammon;Naharai from Beeroth, the armor bearer of Joab son
        of Zeruiah;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Ira from Jattir;Gareb from Jattir;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Uriah the Hittite;Zabad son of Ahlai;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Adina son of Shiza, the Reubenite leader who had thirty men with
        him;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Hanan son of Maacah;Joshaphat from Mithna;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Uzzia from Ashtaroth;Shama and Jeiel, the sons of Hotham, from Aroer;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jediael son of Shimri;Joha, his brother, from Tiz;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Eliel from Mahavah;Jeribai and Joshaviah, the sons of Elnaam;Ithmah
        from Moab;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Eliel and Obed;Jaasiel from Zobah.[[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: '11:47 '
        content: Or <b>the Mezobaite.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Warriors Join David\u2019s Army"
      title: "Warriors Join David\u2019s Army"
      number: 1
      content: '  The following men joined David at Ziklag while he was hiding from
        Saul son of Kish. They were among the warriors who fought beside David in
        battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'All of them were expert archers, and they could shoot arrows or sling
        stones with their left hand as well as their right. They were all relatives
        of Saul from the tribe of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Their leader was Ahiezer son of Shemaah from Gibeah; his brother
        Joash was second-in-command. These were the other warriors:Jeziel and Pelet,
        sons of Azmaveth;Beracah;Jehu from Anathoth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ishmaiah from Gibeon, a famous warrior and leader among the Thirty; 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, and Jozabad from Gederah;  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:4 '
        content: '  Verses 12:4b-40 are numbered 12:5-41 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Eluzai, Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah, and Shephatiah from Haruph;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Elkanah, Isshiah, Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam, who were Korahites;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Joelah and Zebadiah, sons of Jeroham from Gedor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Some brave and experienced warriors from the tribe of Gad also defected
        to David while he was at the stronghold in the wilderness. They were expert
        with both shield and spear, as fierce as lions and as swift as deer on the
        mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ezer was their leader.Obadiah was second.Eliab was third.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Mishmannah was fourth.Jeremiah was fifth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Attai was sixth.Eliel was seventh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Johanan was eighth.Elzabad was ninth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jeremiah was tenth.Macbannai was eleventh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These warriors from Gad were army commanders. The weakest among them
        could take on a hundred regular troops, and the strongest could take on a
        thousand! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These were the men who crossed the Jordan River during its seasonal
        flooding at the beginning of the year and drove out all the people living
        in the lowlands on both the east and west banks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Others from Benjamin and Judah came to David at the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "David went out to meet them and said, \u201CIf you have come in peace
        to help me, we are friends. But if you have come to betray me to my enemies
        when I am innocent, then may the God of our ancestors see it and punish you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Spirit came upon Amasai, the leader of the Thirty, and he
        said,\u201CWe are yours, David!We are on your side, son of Jesse.Peace and
        prosperity be with you,and success to all who help you,for your God is the
        one who helps you.\u201DSo David let them join him, and he made them officers
        over his troops.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Some men from Manasseh defected from the Israelite army and joined
        David when he set out with the Philistines to fight against Saul. But as
        it turned out, the Philistine rulers refused to let David and his men go
        with them. After much discussion, they sent them back, for they said, \u201CIt
        will cost us our heads if David switches loyalties to Saul and turns against
        us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Here is a list of the men from Manasseh who defected to David as
        he was returning to Ziklag: Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu,
        and Zillethai. Each commanded 1,000 troops from the tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They helped David chase down bands of raiders, for they were all
        brave and able warriors who became commanders in his army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Day after day more men joined David until he had a great army, like
        the army of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These are the numbers of armed warriors who joined David at Hebron.
        They were all eager to see David become king instead of Saul, just as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had promised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'From the tribe of Judah, there were 6,800 warriors armed with shields
        and spears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From the tribe of Simeon, there were 7,100 brave warriors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'From the tribe of Levi, there were 4,600 warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This included Jehoiada, leader of the family of Aaron, who had 3,700
        under his command. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This also included Zadok, a brave young warrior, with 22 members
        of his family who were all officers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "From the tribe of Benjamin, Saul\u2019s relatives, there were 3,000
        warriors. Most of the men from Benjamin had remained loyal to Saul until
        this time.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'From the tribe of Ephraim, there were 20,800 brave warriors, each
        highly respected in his own clan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'From the half-tribe of Manasseh west of the Jordan, 18,000 men were
        designated by name to help David become king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'From the tribe of Issachar, there were 200 leaders of the tribe with
        their relatives. All these men understood the signs of the times and knew
        the best course for Israel to take.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'From the tribe of Zebulun, there were 50,000 skilled warriors. They
        were fully armed and prepared for battle and completely loyal to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'From the tribe of Naphtali, there were 1,000 officers and 37,000
        warriors armed with shields and spears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'From the tribe of Dan, there were 28,600 warriors, all prepared for
        battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From the tribe of Asher, there were 40,000 trained warriors, all
        prepared for battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "From the east side of the Jordan River\u2014where the tribes of Reuben
        and Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh lived\u2014there were 120,000 troops
        armed with every kind of weapon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'All these men came in battle array to Hebron with the single purpose
        of making David the king over all Israel. In fact, everyone in Israel agreed
        that David should be their king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'They feasted and drank with David for three days, for preparations
        had been made by their relatives for their arrival. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: And people from as far away as Issachar, Zebulun, and Naphtali brought
        food on donkeys, camels, mules, and oxen. Vast supplies of flour, fig cakes,
        clusters of raisins, wine, olive oil, cattle, sheep, and goats were brought
        to the celebration. There was great joy throughout the land of Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Attempts to Move the Ark'
      title: David Attempts to Move the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  David consulted with all his officials, including the generals
        and captains of his army.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the commanders of thousands and of hundreds.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he addressed the entire assembly of Israel as follows: \u201CIf
        you approve and if it is the will of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God, let us send messages to all the Israelites throughout the land, including
        the priests and Levites in their towns and pasturelands. Let us invite them
        to come and join us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It is time to bring back the Ark of our God, for we neglected it
        during the reign of Saul.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The whole assembly agreed to this, for the people could see it was
        the right thing to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So David summoned all Israel, from the Shihor Brook of Egypt in the
        south all the way to the town of Lebo-hamath in the north, to join in bringing
        the Ark of God from Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then David and all Israel went to Baalah of Judah (also called Kiriath-jearim)
        to bring back the Ark of God, which bears the name[[COMMENT(0)]] of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who is enthroned between the cherubim. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: "Or <b>the Ark of God, where the Name is proclaimed\u2014the name.</b>"
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They placed the Ark of God on a new cart and brought it from Abinadab\u2019s
        house. Uzzah and Ahio were guiding the cart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David and all Israel were celebrating before God with all their might,
        singing songs and playing all kinds of musical instruments\u2014lyres, harps,
        tambourines, cymbals, and trumpets.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But when they arrived at the threshing floor of Nacon,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the oxen stumbled, and Uzzah reached out his hand to steady the Ark. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:9 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 6:6; Hebrew reads <b>Kidon.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger was aroused against
        Uzzah, and he struck him dead because he had laid his hand on the Ark. So
        Uzzah died there in the presence of God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "David was angry because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger
        had burst out against Uzzah. He named that place Perez-uzzah (which means
        \u201Cto burst out against Uzzah\u201D), as it is still called today.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "David was now afraid of God, and he asked, \u201CHow can I ever bring
        the Ark of God back into my care?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David did not move the Ark into the City of David. Instead, he
        took it to the house of Obed-edom of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Ark of God remained there in Obed-edom\u2019s house for three
        months, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> blessed the household of Obed-edom
        and everything he owned."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Palace and Family"
      title: "David\u2019s Palace and Family"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then King Hiram of Tyre sent messengers to David, along with cedar
        timber, and stonemasons and carpenters to build him a palace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David realized that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had confirmed
        him as king over Israel and had greatly blessed his kingdom for the sake
        of his people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then David married more wives in Jerusalem, and they had more sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "These are the names of David\u2019s sons who were born in Jerusalem:
        Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: David Conquers the Philistines'
      title: David Conquers the Philistines
      number: 7
      content: 'Elishama, Eliada,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Eliphelet.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Beeliada, </b>a variant spelling of Eliada; compare 3:8
          and parallel text at 2 Sam 5:16.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over
        all Israel, they mobilized all their forces to capture him. But David was
        told they were coming, so he marched out to meet them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Philistines arrived and made a raid in the valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So David asked God, \u201CShould I go out to fight the Philistines?
        Will you hand them over to me?\u201DThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied,
        \u201CYes, go ahead. I will hand them over to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So David and his troops went up to Baal-perazim and defeated the
        Philistines there. \u201CGod did it!\u201D David exclaimed. \u201CHe used
        me to burst through my enemies like a raging flood!\u201D So they named that
        place Baal-perazim (which means \u201Cthe Lord who bursts through\u201D). "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Philistines had abandoned their gods there, so David gave orders
        to burn them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But after a while the Philistines returned and raided the valley
        again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And once again David asked God what to do. \u201CDo not attack them
        straight on,\u201D God replied. \u201CInstead, circle around behind and attack
        them near the poplar[[COMMENT(0)]] trees. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:14 '
        content: Or <b>aspen, </b>or <b>balsam; </b>also in 14:15. The exact identification
          of this tree is uncertain.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When you hear a sound like marching feet in the tops of the poplar
        trees, go out and attack! That will be the signal that God is moving ahead
        of you to strike down the Philistine army.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So David did what God commanded, and they struck down the Philistine
        army all the way from Gibeon to Gezer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So David\u2019s fame spread everywhere, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        caused all the nations to fear David."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Preparing to Move the Ark'
      title: Preparing to Move the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  David now built several buildings for himself in the City of David.
        He also prepared a place for the Ark of God and set up a special tent for
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he commanded, \u201CNo one except the Levites may carry the
        Ark of God. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen them to carry the
        Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and to serve him forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then David summoned all Israel to Jerusalem to bring the Ark of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to the place he had prepared for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is the number of the descendants of Aaron (the priests) and
        the Levites who were called together:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'From the clan of Kohath, 120, with Uriel as their leader.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'From the clan of Merari, 220, with Asaiah as their leader.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'From the clan of Gershon,[[COMMENT(0)]] 130, with Joel as their leader.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Gershom, </b>a variant spelling of Gershon.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'From the descendants of Elizaphan, 200, with Shemaiah as their leader.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'From the descendants of Hebron, 80, with Eliel as their leader.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'From the descendants of Uzziel, 112, with Amminadab as their leader.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David summoned the priests, Zadok and Abiathar, and these Levite
        leaders: Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and Amminadab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He said to them, \u201CYou are the leaders of the Levite families.
        You must purify yourselves and all your fellow Levites, so you can bring
        the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, to the place
        I have prepared for it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Because you Levites did not carry the Ark the first time, the anger
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God burst out against us. We failed
        to ask God how to move it properly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the priests and the Levites purified themselves in order to bring
        the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Levites carried the Ark of God on their shoulders with its
        carrying poles, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had instructed Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David also ordered the Levite leaders to appoint a choir of Levites
        who were singers and musicians to sing joyful songs to the accompaniment
        of harps, lyres, and cymbals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the Levites appointed Heman son of Joel along with his fellow
        Levites: Asaph son of Berekiah, and Ethan son of Kushaiah from the clan of
        Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The following men were chosen as their assistants: Zechariah, Jaaziel,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah, Eliphelehu,
        Mikneiah, and the gatekeepers\u2014Obed-edom and Jeiel.  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:18 '
        content: As in several Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version (see also parallel
          lists in 15:20; 16:5); Masoretic Text reads <b>Zechariah ben Jaaziel.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The musicians Heman, Asaph, and Ethan were chosen to sound the bronze
        cymbals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and
        Benaiah were chosen to play the harps.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:20 '
        content: Hebrew adds <b>according to Alamoth, </b>which is probably a musical
          term. The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah were
        chosen to play the lyres.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:21 '
        content: Hebrew adds <b>according to the Sheminith, </b>which is probably
          a musical term. The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Kenaniah, the head Levite, was chosen as the choir leader because
        of his skill.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Berekiah and Elkanah were chosen to guard[[COMMENT(0)]] the Ark. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>chosen as gatekeepers for; </b>also in 15:24.
    - name: '24: Moving the Ark to Jerusalem'
      title: Moving the Ark to Jerusalem
      number: 24
      content: "Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah, and Eliezer\u2014all
        of whom were priests\u2014were chosen to blow the trumpets as they marched
        in front of the Ark of God. Obed-edom and Jehiah were chosen to guard the
        Ark.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then David and the elders of Israel and the generals of the army[[COMMENT(0)]]
        went to the house of Obed-edom to bring the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant up to Jerusalem with a great celebration. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:25 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the commanders of thousands.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And because God was clearly helping the Levites as they carried the
        Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Covenant, they sacrificed seven
        bulls and seven rams.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'David was dressed in a robe of fine linen, as were all the Levites
        who carried the Ark, and also the singers, and Kenaniah the choir leader.
        David was also wearing a priestly garment.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:27 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a linen ephod.</b>
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So all Israel brought up the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant with shouts of joy, the blowing of rams\u2019 horns and trumpets,
        the crashing of cymbals, and loud playing on harps and lyres.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But as the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Covenant
        entered the City of David, Michal, the daughter of Saul, looked down from
        her window. When she saw King David skipping about and laughing with joy,
        she was filled with contempt for him."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  They brought the Ark of God and placed it inside the special tent
        David had prepared for it. And they presented burnt offerings and peace offerings
        to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When he had finished his sacrifices, David blessed the people in
        the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then he gave to every man and woman in all Israel a loaf of bread,
        a cake of dates,[[COMMENT(0)]] and a cake of raisins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:3 '
        content: Or <b>a portion of meat. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "David appointed the following Levites to lead the people in worship
        before the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014to invoke his blessings,
        to give thanks, and to praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Asaph, the leader of this group, sounded the cymbals. Second to him
        was Zechariah, followed by Jeiel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab,
        Benaiah, Obed-edom, and Jeiel. They played the harps and lyres. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: David\u2019s Song of Praise"
      title: "David\u2019s Song of Praise"
      number: 6
      content: "The priests, Benaiah and Jahaziel, played the trumpets regularly
        before the Ark of God\u2019s Covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'On that day David gave to Asaph and his fellow Levites this song
        of thanksgiving to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and proclaim his greatness.Let
        the whole world know what he has done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sing to him; yes, sing his praises.Tell everyone about his wonderful
        deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Exult in his holy name;rejoice, you who worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Search for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and for his strength;continually
        seek him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Remember the wonders he has performed,his miracles, and the rulings
        he has given,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'you children of his servant Israel,you descendants of Jacob, his
        chosen ones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.His justice is seen
        throughout the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Remember his covenant forever\u2014the commitment he made to a thousand
        generations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This is the covenant he made with Abrahamand the oath he swore to
        Isaac.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He confirmed it to Jacob as a decree,and to the people of Israel
        as a never-ending covenant:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CI will give you the land of Canaanas your special possession.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He said this when you were few in number,a tiny group of strangers
        in Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They wandered from nation to nation,from one kingdom to another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yet he did not let anyone oppress them.He warned kings on their behalf:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CDo not touch my chosen people,and do not hurt my prophets.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let the whole earth sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Each
        day proclaim the good news that he saves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Publish his glorious deeds among the nations.Tell everyone about
        the amazing things he does.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Great is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! He is most worthy of praise!He
        is to be feared above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The gods of other nations are mere idols,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        made the heavens!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Honor and majesty surround him;strength and joy fill his dwelling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'O nations of the world, recognize the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,recognize
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is glorious and strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Give to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> the glory he deserves!Bring
        your offering and come into his presence.Worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in all his holy splendor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Let all the earth tremble before him.The world stands firm and cannot
        be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Let the heavens be glad, and the earth rejoice!Tell all the nations,
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reigns!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let the sea and everything in it shout his praise!Let the fields
        and their crops burst out with joy!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Let the trees of the forest sing for joy before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for
        he is coming to judge the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he is good!His
        faithful love endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Cry out, \u201CSave us, O God of our salvation!Gather and rescue
        us from among the nations,so we can thank your holy nameand rejoice and praise
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Worship at Jerusalem and Gibeon'
      title: Worship at Jerusalem and Gibeon
      number: 36
      content: "Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,who lives
        from everlasting to everlasting!And all the people shouted \u201CAmen!\u201D
        and praised the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "David arranged for Asaph and his fellow Levites to serve regularly
        before the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Covenant, doing
        whatever needed to be done each day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'This group included Obed-edom (son of Jeduthun), Hosah, and sixty-eight
        other Levites as gatekeepers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Meanwhile, David stationed Zadok the priest and his fellow priests
        at the Tabernacle of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the place of worship
        in Gibeon, where they continued to minister before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'They sacrificed the regular burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        each morning and evening on the altar set aside for that purpose, obeying
        everything written in the Law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, as he had
        commanded Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "David also appointed Heman, Jeduthun, and the others chosen by name
        to give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for \u201Chis faithful
        love endures forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They used their trumpets, cymbals, and other instruments to accompany
        their songs of praise to God.[[COMMENT(0)]] And the sons of Jeduthun were
        appointed as gatekeepers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:42 '
        content: Or <b>to accompany the sacred music; </b>or <b>to accompany singing
          to God.</b>
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Then all the people returned to their homes, and David turned and
        went home to bless his own family.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Covenant Promise to David"
      title: "The \u2019s Covenant Promise to David"
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  When David was settled in his palace,
        he summoned Nathan the prophet. \u201CLook,\u201D David said, \u201CI am
        living in a beautiful cedar palace,[[COMMENT(0)]] but the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant is out there under a tent!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a house of cedar.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Nathan replied to David, \u201CDo whatever you have in mind, for
        God is with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But that same night God said to Nathan,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo and tell my servant David, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has declared: You are not the one to build a house for me to live in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I have never lived in a house, from the day I brought the Israelites
        out of Egypt until this very day. My home has always been a tent, moving
        from one place to another in a Tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Yet no matter where I have gone with the Israelites, I have never
        once complained to Israel\u2019s leaders, the shepherds of my people. I have
        never asked them, \u201CWhy haven\u2019t you built me a beautiful cedar house?\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CNow go and say to my servant David, \u2018This is what the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has declared: I took
        you from tending sheep in the pasture and selected you to be the leader of
        my people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I have been with you wherever you have gone, and I have destroyed
        all your enemies before your eyes. Now I will make your name as famous as
        anyone who has ever lived on the earth! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will provide a homeland for my people Israel, planting them
        in a secure place where they will never be disturbed. Evil nations won\u2019t
        oppress them as they\u2019ve done in the past, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "starting from the time I appointed judges to rule my people Israel.
        And I will defeat all your enemies.\u201C\u2018Furthermore, I declare that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will build a house for you\u2014a dynasty
        of kings! "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For when you die and join your ancestors, I will raise up one of
        your descendants, one of your sons, and I will make his kingdom strong. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He is the one who will build a house\u2014a temple\u2014for me. And
        I will secure his throne forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will be his father, and he will be my son. I will never take my
        favor from him as I took it from the one who ruled before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will confirm him as king over my house and my kingdom for all time,
        and his throne will be secure forever.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: David\u2019s Prayer of Thanks"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer of Thanks"
      number: 15
      content: 'So Nathan went back to David and told him everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had said in this vision.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then King David went in and sat before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and prayed,\u201CWho am I, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God, and what is
        my family, that you have brought me this far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And now, O God, in addition to everything else, you speak of giving
        your servant a lasting dynasty! You speak as though I were someone very great,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God!  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:17 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CWhat more can I say to you about the way you have honored me?
        You know what your servant is really like. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the sake of your servant, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        according to your will, you have done all these great things and have made
        them known.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, there is no one like you. We
        have never even heard of another God like you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'What other nation on earth is like your people Israel? What other
        nation, O God, have you redeemed from slavery to be your own people? You
        made a great name for yourself when you redeemed your people from Egypt.
        You performed awesome miracles and drove out the nations that stood in their
        way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You chose Israel to be your very own people forever, and you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        became their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I am your servant;
        do as you have promised concerning me and my family. May it be a promise
        that will last forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And may your name be established and honored forever so that everyone
        will say, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, is Israel\u2019s God!\u2019 And may the house of your
        servant David continue before you forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CO my God, I have been bold enough to pray to you because you
        have revealed to your servant that you will build a house for him\u2014a
        dynasty of kings! "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For you are God, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And you have promised
        these good things to your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And now, it has pleased you to bless the house of your servant, so
        that it will continue forever before you. For when you grant a blessing,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, it is an eternal blessing!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Military Victories"
      title: "David\u2019s Military Victories"
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, David defeated and subdued the Philistines by conquering
        Gath and its surrounding towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David also conquered the land of Moab, and the Moabites who were
        spared became David\u2019s subjects and paid him tribute money.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David also destroyed the forces of Hadadezer, king of Zobah, as far
        as Hamath,[[COMMENT(0)]] when Hadadezer marched out to strengthen his control
        along the Euphrates River. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:3 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David captured 1,000 chariots, 7,000 charioteers, and 20,000 foot
        soldiers. He crippled all the chariot horses except enough for 100 chariots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Arameans from Damascus arrived to help King Hadadezer, David
        killed 22,000 of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he placed several army garrisons[[COMMENT(0)]] in Damascus,
        the Aramean capital, and the Arameans became David\u2019s subjects and paid
        him tribute money. So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made David victorious
        wherever he went.  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:6 '
        content: As in Greek version and Latin Vulgate (see also 2 Sam 8:6); Hebrew
          lacks <b>several army garrisons.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "David brought the gold shields of Hadadezer\u2019s officers to Jerusalem, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "along with a large amount of bronze from Hadadezer\u2019s towns of
        Tebah[[COMMENT(0)]] and Cun. Later Solomon melted the bronze and molded it
        into the great bronze basin called the Sea, the pillars, and the various
        bronze articles used at the Temple.  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:8 '
        content: Hebrew reads <b>Tibhath, </b>a variant spelling of Tebah; compare
          parallel text at 2 Sam 8:8.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When King Toi[[COMMENT(0)]] of Hamath heard that David had destroyed
        the entire army of King Hadadezer of Zobah, '
      comments:
      - number: '18:9 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 8:9; Hebrew reads <b>Tou; </b>also
          in 18:10.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he sent his son Joram[[COMMENT(0)]] to congratulate King David for
        his successful campaign. Hadadezer and Toi had been enemies and were often
        at war. Joram presented David with many gifts of gold, silver, and bronze.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:10 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 8:10; Hebrew reads <b>Hadoram, </b>a
          variant spelling of Joram.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "King David dedicated all these gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        along with the silver and gold he had taken from the other nations\u2014from
        Edom, Moab, Ammon, Philistia, and Amalek.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abishai son of Zeruiah destroyed 18,000 Edomites in the Valley of
        Salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He placed army garrisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became David\u2019s
        subjects. In fact, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made David victorious
        wherever he went.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel and did what was just and right
        for all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Joab son of Zeruiah was commander of the army. Jehoshaphat son of
        Ahilud was the royal historian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Zadok son of Ahitub and Ahimelech[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Abiathar were
        the priests. Seraiah[[COMMENT(1)]] was the court secretary. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:16a '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts, Syriac version, and Latin Vulgate
          (see also 2 Sam 8:17); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Abimelech.</b>
      - number: '18:16b '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 8:17; Hebrew reads <b>Shavsha.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Benaiah son of Jehoiada was captain of the king\u2019s bodyguard.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And David\u2019s sons served as the king\u2019s chief assistants."
      comments:
      - number: '18:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of the Kerethites and Pelethites.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Defeats the Ammonites'
      title: David Defeats the Ammonites
      number: 1
      content: '  Some time after this, King Nahash of the Ammonites died, and his
        son Hanun[[COMMENT(0)]] became king. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:1 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 10:1; Hebrew lacks <b>Hanun.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said, \u201CI am going to show loyalty to Hanun because his
        father, Nahash, was always loyal to me.\u201D So David sent messengers to
        express sympathy to Hanun about his father\u2019s death.But when David\u2019s
        ambassadors arrived in the land of Ammon, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "the Ammonite commanders said to Hanun, \u201CDo you really think
        these men are coming here to honor your father? No! David has sent them to
        spy out the land so they can come in and conquer it!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Hanun seized David\u2019s ambassadors and shaved them, cut off
        their robes at the buttocks, and sent them back to David in shame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When David heard what had happened to the men, he sent messengers
        to tell them, \u201CStay at Jericho until your beards grow out, and then
        come back.\u201D For they felt deep shame because of their appearance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the people of Ammon realized how seriously they had angered
        David, Hanun and the Ammonites sent 75,000 pounds[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver
        to hire chariots and charioteers from Aram-naharaim, Aram-maacah, and Zobah. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>1,000 talents </b>[34,000 kilograms].
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They also hired 32,000 chariots and secured the support of the king
        of Maacah and his army. These forces camped at Medeba, where they were joined
        by the Ammonite troops that Hanun had recruited from his own towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When David heard about this, he sent Joab and all his warriors to
        fight them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Ammonite troops came out and drew up their battle lines at the
        entrance of the city, while the other kings positioned themselves to fight
        in the open fields.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When Joab saw that he would have to fight on both the front and the
        rear, he chose some of Israel\u2019s elite troops and placed them under his
        personal command to fight the Arameans in the fields. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He left the rest of the army under the command of his brother Abishai,
        who was to attack the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf the Arameans are too strong for me, then come over and help
        me,\u201D Joab told his brother. \u201CAnd if the Ammonites are too strong
        for you, I will help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Be courageous! Let us fight bravely for our people and the cities
        of our God. May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s will be done.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Joab and his troops attacked, the Arameans began to run away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And when the Ammonites saw the Arameans running, they also ran from
        Abishai and retreated into the city. Then Joab returned to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Arameans now realized that they were no match for Israel, so
        they sent messengers and summoned additional Aramean troops from the other
        side of the Euphrates River.[[COMMENT(0)]] These troops were under the command
        of Shobach,[[COMMENT(1)]] the commander of Hadadezer\u2019s forces.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:16a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
      - number: '19:16b '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 10:16; Hebrew reads <b>Shophach; </b>also
          in 19:18.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When David heard what was happening, he mobilized all Israel, crossed
        the Jordan River, and positioned his troops in battle formation. Then David
        engaged the Arameans in battle, and they fought against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But again the Arameans fled from the Israelites. This time David\u2019s
        forces killed 7,000 charioteers and 40,000 foot soldiers, including Shobach,
        the commander of their army. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When Hadadezer\u2019s allies saw that they had been defeated by Israel,
        they surrendered to David and became his subjects. After that, the Arameans
        were no longer willing to help the Ammonites."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Captures Rabbah'
      title: David Captures Rabbah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the spring of the year,[[COMMENT(0)]] when kings normally go
        out to war, Joab led the Israelite army in successful attacks against the
        land of the Ammonites. In the process he laid siege to the city of Rabbah,
        attacking and destroying it. However, David stayed behind in Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>At the turn of the year. </b>The first day of the year
          in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in March or April.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David went to Rabbah and removed the crown from the king\u2019s
        head,[[COMMENT(0)]] and it was placed on his own head. The crown was made
        of gold and set with gems, and he found that it weighed seventy-five pounds.[[COMMENT(1)]]
        David took a vast amount of plunder from the city. "
      comments:
      - number: '20:2a '
        content: Or <b>from the head of Milcom </b>(as in Greek version and Latin
          Vulgate). Milcom, also called Molech, was the god of the Ammonites.
      - number: '20:2b '
        content: Hebrew <b>1 talent </b>[34 kilograms].
    - name: '3: Battles against Philistine Giants'
      title: Battles against Philistine Giants
      number: 3
      content: 'He also made slaves of the people of Rabbah and forced them to labor
        with saws, iron picks, and iron axes.[[COMMENT(0)]] That is how David dealt
        with the people of all the Ammonite towns. Then David and all the army returned
        to Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 12:31; Hebrew reads <b>and cut them
          with saws, iron picks, and saws.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After this, war broke out with the Philistines at Gezer. As they
        fought, Sibbecai from Hushah killed Saph,[[COMMENT(0)]] a descendant of the
        giants,[[COMMENT(1)]] and so the Philistines were subdued.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:4a '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 21:18; Hebrew reads <b>Sippai.</b>
      - number: '20:4b '
        content: Hebrew <b>descendant of the Rephaites; </b>also in 20:6, 8.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "During another battle with the Philistines, Elhanan son of Jair killed
        Lahmi, the brother of Goliath of Gath. The handle of Lahmi\u2019s spear was
        as thick as a weaver\u2019s beam!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In another battle with the Philistines at Gath, they encountered
        a huge man with six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four
        in all, who was also a descendant of the giants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But when he defied and taunted Israel, he was killed by Jonathan,
        the son of David\u2019s brother Shimea.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: These Philistines were descendants of the giants of Gath, but David
        and his warriors killed them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Takes a Census'
      title: David Takes a Census
      number: 1
      content: '  Satan rose up against Israel and caused David to take a census
        of the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Joab and the commanders of the army, \u201CTake
        a census of all the people of Israel\u2014from Beersheba in the south to
        Dan in the north\u2014and bring me a report so I may know how many there
        are.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Joab replied, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> increase
        the number of his people a hundred times over! But why, my lord the king,
        do you want to do this? Are they not all your servants? Why must you cause
        Israel to sin?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the king insisted that they take the census, so Joab traveled
        throughout all Israel to count the people. Then he returned to Jerusalem '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and reported the number of people to David. There were 1,100,000
        warriors in all Israel who could handle a sword, and 470,000 in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Judgment for David\u2019s Sin"
      title: "Judgment for David\u2019s Sin"
      number: 6
      content: 'But Joab did not include the tribes of Levi and Benjamin in the census
        because he was so distressed at what the king had made him do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'God was very displeased with the census, and he punished Israel for
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to God, \u201CI have sinned greatly by taking this
        census. Please forgive my guilt for doing this foolish thing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Gad, David\u2019s seer.
        This was the message: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo and say to David, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: I will give you three choices. Choose one of these punishments, and
        I will inflict it on you.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Gad came to David and said, \u201CThese are the choices the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You may choose three years of famine, three months of destruction
        by the sword of your enemies, or three days of severe plague as the angel
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brings devastation throughout the land
        of Israel. Decide what answer I should give the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who sent me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI\u2019m in a desperate situation!\u201D David replied to Gad.
        \u201CBut let me fall into the hands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for his mercy is very great. Do not let me fall into human hands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent a plague upon Israel, and
        70,000 people died as a result. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And God sent an angel to destroy Jerusalem. But just as the angel
        was preparing to destroy it, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relented and
        said to the death angel, \u201CStop! That is enough!\u201D At that moment
        the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was standing by the threshing
        floor of Araunah[[COMMENT(0)]] the Jebusite.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:15 '
        content: As in parallel text at 2 Sam 24:16; Hebrew reads <b>Ornan, </b>another
          name for Araunah; also in 21:18-28.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David looked up and saw the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        standing between heaven and earth with his sword drawn, reaching out over
        Jerusalem. So David and the leaders of Israel put on burlap to show their
        deep distress and fell face down on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: David Builds an Altar'
      title: David Builds an Altar
      number: 17
      content: "And David said to God, \u201CI am the one who called for the census!
        I am the one who has sinned and done wrong! But these people are as innocent
        as sheep\u2014what have they done? O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God,
        let your anger fall against me and my family, but do not destroy your people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told Gad to instruct
        David to go up and build an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the
        threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So David went up to do what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        him through Gad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Araunah, who was busy threshing wheat at the time, turned and saw
        the angel there. His four sons, who were with him, ran away and hid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Araunah saw David approaching, he left his threshing floor and
        bowed before David with his face to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "David said to Araunah, \u201CLet me buy this threshing floor from
        you at its full price. Then I will build an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        there, so that he will stop the plague.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CTake it, my lord the king, and use it as you wish,\u201D Araunah
        said to David. \u201CI will give the oxen for the burnt offerings, and the
        threshing boards for wood to build a fire on the altar, and the wheat for
        the grain offering. I will give it all to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But King David replied to Araunah, \u201CNo, I insist on buying it
        for the full price. I will not take what is yours and give it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        I will not present burnt offerings that have cost me nothing!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So David gave Araunah 600 pieces of gold[[COMMENT(0)]] in payment
        for the threshing floor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:25 '
        content: Hebrew <b>600 shekels of gold, </b>about 15 pounds or 6.8 kilograms
          in weight.
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'David built an altar there to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        sacrificed burnt offerings and peace offerings. And when David prayed, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered him by sending fire from heaven to burn
        up the offering on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to the angel, who put
        the sword back into its sheath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When David saw that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had answered
        his prayer, he offered sacrifices there at Araunah\u2019s threshing floor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'At that time the Tabernacle of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        the altar of burnt offering that Moses had made in the wilderness were located
        at the place of worship in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But David was not able to go there to inquire of God, because he was
        terrified by the drawn sword of the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Preparations for the Temple'
      title: Preparations for the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "  Then David said, \u201CThis will be the location for the Temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God and the place of the altar for Israel\u2019s
        burnt offerings!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David gave orders to call together the foreigners living in Israel,
        and he assigned them the task of preparing finished stone for building the
        Temple of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David provided large amounts of iron for the nails that would be
        needed for the doors in the gates and for the clamps, and he gave more bronze
        than could be weighed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He also provided innumerable cedar logs, for the men of Tyre and
        Sidon had brought vast amounts of cedar to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David said, \u201CMy son Solomon is still young and inexperienced.
        And since the Temple to be built for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> must
        be a magnificent structure, famous and glorious throughout the world, I will
        begin making preparations for it now.\u201D So David collected vast amounts
        of building materials before his death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then David sent for his son Solomon and instructed him to build a
        Temple for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CMy son, I wanted to build a Temple to honor the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God,\u201D David told him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018You have
        killed many men in the battles you have fought. And since you have shed so
        much blood in my sight, you will not be the one to build a Temple to honor
        my name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But you will have a son who will be a man of peace. I will give him
        peace with his enemies in all the surrounding lands. His name will be Solomon,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and I will give peace and quiet to Israel during his reign. '
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        content: "<b>Solomon </b>sounds like and is probably derived from the Hebrew
          word for \u201Cpeace.\u201D"
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He is the one who will build a Temple to honor my name. He will be
        my son, and I will be his father. And I will secure the throne of his kingdom
        over Israel forever.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNow, my son, may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be with you
        and give you success as you follow his directions in building the Temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> give you wisdom and understanding,
        that you may obey the Law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God as
        you rule over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For you will be successful if you carefully obey the decrees and
        regulations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave to Israel through Moses.
        Be strong and courageous; do not be afraid or lose heart!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI have worked hard to provide materials for building the Temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014nearly 4,000 tons of gold, 40,000
        tons of silver,[[COMMENT(0)]] and so much iron and bronze that it cannot
        be weighed. I have also gathered timber and stone for the walls, though you
        may need to add more. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>100,000 talents </b>[3,400 metric tons] <b>of gold, 1,000,000
          talents </b>[34,000 metric tons] <b>of silver.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You have a large number of skilled stonemasons and carpenters and
        craftsmen of every kind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You have expert goldsmiths and silversmiths and workers of bronze
        and iron. Now begin the work, and may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be
        with you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David ordered all the leaders of Israel to assist Solomon in
        this project. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is with you,\u201D
        he declared. \u201CHe has given you peace with the surrounding nations. He
        has handed them over to me, and they are now subject to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and his people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with all your heart
        and soul. Build the sanctuary of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God so that
        you can bring the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Covenant
        and the holy vessels of God into the Temple built to honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        name.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Duties of the Levites'
      title: Duties of the Levites
      number: 1
      content: '  When David was an old man, he appointed his son Solomon to be king
        over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'David summoned all the leaders of Israel, together with the priests
        and Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All the Levites who were thirty years old or older were counted,
        and the total came to 38,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then David said, \u201CFrom all the Levites, 24,000 will supervise
        the work at the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Another 6,000
        will serve as officials and judges. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Another 4,000 will work as gatekeepers, and 4,000 will praise the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with the musical instruments I have made.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Gershonites'
      title: The Gershonites
      number: 6
      content: "Then David divided the Levites into divisions named after the clans
        descended from the three sons of Levi\u2014Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Gershonite family units were defined by their lines of descent
        from Libni[[COMMENT(0)]] and Shimei, the sons of Gershon. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ladan </b>(also in 23:8, 9), a variant spelling of Libni;
          compare 6:17.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Three of the descendants of Libni were Jehiel (the family leader),
        Zetham, and Joel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These were the leaders of the family of Libni.Three of the descendants
        of Shimei were Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Four other descendants of Shimei were Jahath, Ziza,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Jeush, and Beriah. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:10 '
        content: As in Greek version and Latin Vulgate (see also 23:11); Hebrew reads
          <b>Zina.</b>
    - name: '11: The Kohathites'
      title: The Kohathites
      number: 11
      content: 'Jahath was the family leader, and Ziza was next. Jeush and Beriah
        were counted as a single family because neither had many sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Four of the descendants of Kohath were Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and
        Uzziel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The sons of Amram were Aaron and Moses. Aaron and his descendants
        were set apart to dedicate the most holy things, to offer sacrifices in the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence, to serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and to pronounce blessings in his name forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As for Moses, the man of God, his sons were included with the tribe
        of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Moses were Gershom and Eliezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The descendants of Gershom included Shebuel, the family leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Eliezer had only one son, Rehabiah, the family leader. Rehabiah had
        numerous descendants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The descendants of Izhar included Shelomith, the family leader.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The descendants of Hebron included Jeriah (the family leader), Amariah
        (the second), Jahaziel (the third), and Jekameam (the fourth).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Merarites'
      title: The Merarites
      number: 20
      content: 'The descendants of Uzziel included Micah (the family leader) and
        Isshiah (the second).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The descendants of Merari included Mahli and Mushi.The sons of Mahli
        were Eleazar and Kish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Eleazar died with no sons, only daughters. His daughters married
        their cousins, the sons of Kish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Three of the descendants of Mushi were Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These were the descendants of Levi by clans, the leaders of their
        family groups, registered carefully by name. Each had to be twenty years
        old or older to qualify for service in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, has given us peace, and he will always live in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now the Levites will no longer need to carry the Tabernacle and its
        furnishings from place to place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "In accordance with David\u2019s final instructions, all the Levites
        twenty years old or older were registered for service.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The work of the Levites was to assist the priests, the descendants
        of Aaron, as they served at the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        They also took care of the courtyards and side rooms, helped perform the
        ceremonies of purification, and served in many other ways in the house of
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They were in charge of the sacred bread that was set out on the table,
        the choice flour for the grain offerings, the wafers made without yeast,
        the cakes cooked in olive oil, and the other mixed breads. They were also
        responsible to check all the weights and measures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And each morning and evening they stood before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to sing songs of thanks and praise to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "They assisted with the burnt offerings that were presented to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on Sabbath days, at new moon celebrations, and
        at all the appointed festivals. The required number of Levites served in
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence at all times, following all
        the procedures they had been given.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And so, under the supervision of the priests, the Levites watched
        over the Tabernacle and the Temple[[COMMENT(0)]] and faithfully carried out
        their duties of service at the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments:
      - number: '23:32 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Tent of Meeting and the sanctuary.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Duties of the Priests'
      title: Duties of the Priests
      number: 1
      content: "  This is how Aaron\u2019s descendants, the priests, were divided
        into groups for service. The sons of Aaron were Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and
        Ithamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But Nadab and Abihu died before their father, and they had no sons.
        So only Eleazar and Ithamar were left to carry on as priests.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "With the help of Zadok, who was a descendant of Eleazar, and of Ahimelech,
        who was a descendant of Ithamar, David divided Aaron\u2019s descendants into
        groups according to their various duties. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Eleazar\u2019s descendants were divided into sixteen groups and Ithamar\u2019s
        into eight, for there were more family leaders among the descendants of Eleazar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All tasks were assigned to the various groups by means of sacred
        lots so that no preference would be shown, for there were many qualified
        officials serving God in the sanctuary from among the descendants of both
        Eleazar and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Shemaiah son of Nethanel, a Levite, acted as secretary and wrote
        down the names and assignments in the presence of the king, the officials,
        Zadok the priest, Ahimelech son of Abiathar, and the family leaders of the
        priests and Levites. The descendants of Eleazar and Ithamar took turns casting
        lots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The first lot fell to Jehoiarib.The second lot fell to Jedaiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The third lot fell to Harim.The fourth lot fell to Seorim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The fifth lot fell to Malkijah.The sixth lot fell to Mijamin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The seventh lot fell to Hakkoz.The eighth lot fell to Abijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The ninth lot fell to Jeshua.The tenth lot fell to Shecaniah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The eleventh lot fell to Eliashib.The twelfth lot fell to Jakim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The thirteenth lot fell to Huppah.The fourteenth lot fell to Jeshebeab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The fifteenth lot fell to Bilgah.The sixteenth lot fell to Immer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The seventeenth lot fell to Hezir.The eighteenth lot fell to Happizzez.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The nineteenth lot fell to Pethahiah.The twentieth lot fell to Jehezkel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The twenty-first lot fell to Jakin.The twenty-second lot fell to
        Gamul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The twenty-third lot fell to Delaiah.The twenty-fourth lot fell to
        Maaziah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Family Leaders among the Levites'
      title: Family Leaders among the Levites
      number: 19
      content: 'Each group carried out its appointed duties in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        according to the procedures established by their ancestor Aaron in obedience
        to the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These were the other family leaders descended from Levi:From the
        descendants of Amram, the leader was Shebuel.[[COMMENT(0)]]From the descendants
        of Shebuel, the leader was Jehdeiah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shubael </b>(also in 24:20b), a variant spelling of Shebuel;
          compare 23:16 and 26:24.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'From the descendants of Rehabiah, the leader was Isshiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'From the descendants of Izhar, the leader was Shelomith.[[COMMENT(0)]]From
        the descendants of Shelomith, the leader was Jahath.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shelomoth </b>(also in 24:22b), a variant spelling of
          Shelomith; compare 23:18.
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'From the descendants of Hebron, Jeriah was the leader,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Amariah was second, Jahaziel was third, and Jekameam was fourth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>From the descendants of Jeriah; </b>compare 23:19.
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'From the descendants of Uzziel, the leader was Micah.From the descendants
        of Micah, the leader was Shamir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'along with Isshiah, the brother of Micah.From the descendants of
        Isshiah, the leader was Zechariah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'From the descendants of Merari, the leaders were Mahli and Mushi.From
        the descendants of Jaaziah, the leader was Beno.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'From the descendants of Merari through Jaaziah, the leaders were
        Beno, Shoham, Zaccur, and Ibri.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'From the descendants of Mahli, the leader was Eleazar, though he
        had no sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From the descendants of Kish, the leader was Jerahmeel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'From the descendants of Mushi, the leaders were Mahli, Eder, and
        Jerimoth.These were the descendants of Levi in their various families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Like the descendants of Aaron, they were assigned to their duties
        by means of sacred lots, without regard to age or rank. Lots were drawn in
        the presence of King David, Zadok, Ahimelech, and the family leaders of the
        priests and the Levites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Duties of the Musicians'
      title: Duties of the Musicians
      number: 1
      content: "  David and the army commanders then appointed men from the families
        of Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun to proclaim God\u2019s messages to the accompaniment
        of lyres, harps, and cymbals. Here is a list of their names and their work:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "From the sons of Asaph, there were Zaccur, Joseph, Nethaniah, and
        Asarelah. They worked under the direction of their father, Asaph, who proclaimed
        God\u2019s messages by the king\u2019s orders.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "From the sons of Jeduthun, there were Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six in all. They worked under the direction of
        their father, Jeduthun, who proclaimed God\u2019s messages to the accompaniment
        of the lyre, offering thanks and praise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:3 '
        content: As in one Hebrew manuscript and some Greek manuscripts (see also
          25:17); most Hebrew manuscripts lack <b>Shimei.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From the sons of Heman, there were Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shubael,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah,
        Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shebuel, </b>a variant spelling of Shubael; compare 25:20.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "All these were the sons of Heman, the king\u2019s seer, for God had
        honored him with fourteen sons and three daughters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All these men were under the direction of their fathers as they made
        music at the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Their responsibilities
        included the playing of cymbals, harps, and lyres at the house of God. Asaph,
        Jeduthun, and Heman reported directly to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They and their families were all trained in making music before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and each of them\u2014288 in all\u2014was an
        accomplished musician. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The musicians were appointed to their term of service by means of
        sacred lots, without regard to whether they were young or old, teacher or
        student.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The first lot fell to Joseph of the Asaph clan and twelve of his
        sons and relatives.[[COMMENT(0)]]The second lot fell to Gedaliah and twelve
        of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:9 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew lacks <b>and twelve of his sons and
          relatives.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The third lot fell to Zaccur and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The fourth lot fell to Zeri[[COMMENT(0)]] and twelve of his sons
        and relatives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Izri, </b>a variant spelling of Zeri; compare 25:3.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The fifth lot fell to Nethaniah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sixth lot fell to Bukkiah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The seventh lot fell to Asarelah[[COMMENT(0)]] and twelve of his
        sons and relatives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jesarelah, </b>a variant spelling of Asarelah; compare
          25:2.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The eighth lot fell to Jeshaiah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The ninth lot fell to Mattaniah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The tenth lot fell to Shimei and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The eleventh lot fell to Uzziel[[COMMENT(0)]] and twelve of his sons
        and relatives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Azarel, </b>a variant spelling of Uzziel; compare 25:4.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The twelfth lot fell to Hashabiah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The thirteenth lot fell to Shubael and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The fourteenth lot fell to Mattithiah and twelve of his sons and
        relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The fifteenth lot fell to Jerimoth[[COMMENT(0)]] and twelve of his
        sons and relatives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeremoth, </b>a variant spelling of Jerimoth; compare
          25:4.
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sixteenth lot fell to Hananiah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The seventeenth lot fell to Joshbekashah[[COMMENT(0)]] and twelve
        of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:24 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Joshbekasha, </b>a variant spelling of Joshbekashah; compare
          25:4.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The eighteenth lot fell to Hanani and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The nineteenth lot fell to Mallothi and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The twentieth lot fell to Eliathah and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The twenty-first lot fell to Hothir and twelve of his sons and relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The twenty-second lot fell to Giddalti and twelve of his sons and
        relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The twenty-third lot fell to Mahazioth and twelve of his sons and
        relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The twenty-fourth lot fell to Romamti-ezer and twelve of his sons
        and relatives.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Duties of the Gatekeepers'
      title: Duties of the Gatekeepers
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the divisions of the gatekeepers:From the Korahites,
        there was Meshelemiah son of Kore, of the family of Abiasaph.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:1 '
        content: As in Greek version (see also Exod 6:24); Hebrew reads <b>Asaph.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Meshelemiah were Zechariah (the oldest), Jediael (the
        second), Zebadiah (the third), Jathniel (the fourth), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elam (the fifth), Jehohanan (the sixth), and Eliehoenai (the seventh).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Obed-edom, also gatekeepers, were Shemaiah (the oldest),
        Jehozabad (the second), Joah (the third), Sacar (the fourth), Nethanel (the
        fifth), '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ammiel (the sixth), Issachar (the seventh), and Peullethai (the eighth).
        God had richly blessed Obed-edom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Obed-edom\u2019s son Shemaiah had sons with great ability who earned
        positions of great authority in the clan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Their names were Othni, Rephael, Obed, and Elzabad. Their relatives,
        Elihu and Semakiah, were also very capable men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All of these descendants of Obed-edom, including their sons and grandsons\u2014sixty-two
        of them in all\u2014were very capable men, well qualified for their work.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Meshelemiah\u2019s eighteen sons and relatives were also very capable
        men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hosah, of the Merari clan, appointed Shimri as the leader among his
        sons, though he was not the oldest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "His other sons included Hilkiah (the second), Tebaliah (the third),
        and Zechariah (the fourth). Hosah\u2019s sons and relatives, who served as
        gatekeepers, numbered thirteen in all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'These divisions of the gatekeepers were named for their family leaders,
        and like the other Levites, they served at the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They were assigned by families for guard duty at the various gates,
        without regard to age or training, for it was all decided by means of sacred
        lots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The responsibility for the east gate went to Meshelemiah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and his group. The north gate was assigned to his son Zechariah, a man of
        unusual wisdom. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shelemiah, </b>a variant spelling of Meshelemiah; compare
          26:2.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The south gate went to Obed-edom, and his sons were put in charge
        of the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Shuppim and Hosah were assigned the west gate and the gateway leading
        up to the Temple.[[COMMENT(0)]] Guard duties were divided evenly. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:16 '
        content: Or <b>the gate of Shalleketh on the upper road </b>(also in 26:18).
          The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Six Levites were assigned each day to the east gate, four to the
        north gate, four to the south gate, and two pairs at the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Six were assigned each day to the west gate, four to the gateway
        leading up to the Temple, and two to the courtyard.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:18 '
        content: Or <b>the colonnade. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '19: Treasurers and Other Officials'
      title: Treasurers and Other Officials
      number: 19
      content: 'These were the divisions of the gatekeepers from the clans of Korah
        and Merari.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Other Levites, led by Ahijah, were in charge of the treasuries of
        the house of God and the treasuries of the gifts dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'From the family of Libni[[COMMENT(0)]] in the clan of Gershon, Jehiel[[COMMENT(1)]]
        was the leader. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:21a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ladan, </b>a variant spelling of Libni; compare 6:17.
      - number: '26:21b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jehieli </b>(also in 26:22), a variant spelling of Jehiel;
          compare 23:8.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Jehiel, Zetham and his brother Joel, were in charge of
        the treasuries of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These are the leaders that descended from Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and
        Uzziel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'From the clan of Amram, Shebuel was a descendant of Gershom son of
        Moses. He was the chief officer of the treasuries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'His relatives through Eliezer were Rehabiah, Jeshaiah, Joram, Zicri,
        and Shelomoth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Shelomoth and his relatives were in charge of the treasuries containing
        the gifts that King David, the family leaders, and the generals and captains[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and other officers of the army had dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:26 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the commanders of thousands and of hundreds.</b>
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'These men dedicated some of the plunder they had gained in battle
        to maintain the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Shelomoth[[COMMENT(0)]] and his relatives also cared for the gifts
        dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by Samuel the seer, Saul son
        of Kish, Abner son of Ner, and Joab son of Zeruiah. All the other dedicated
        gifts were in their care, too.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:28 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shelomith, </b>a variant spelling of Shelomoth.
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From the clan of Izhar came Kenaniah. He and his sons were given
        administrative responsibilities[[COMMENT(0)]] over Israel as officials and
        judges.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:29 '
        content: Or <b>were given outside work; </b>or <b>were given work away from
          the Temple area.</b>
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "From the clan of Hebron came Hashabiah. He and his relatives\u20141,700
        capable men\u2014were put in charge of the Israelite lands west of the Jordan
        River. They were responsible for all matters related to the things of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the service of the king in that area.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Also from the clan of Hebron came Jeriah,[[COMMENT(0)]] who was the
        leader of the Hebronites according to the genealogical records. (In the fortieth
        year of David\u2019s reign, a search was made in the records, and capable
        men from the clan of Hebron were found at Jazer in the land of Gilead.) "
      comments:
      - number: '26:31 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jerijah, </b>a variant spelling of Jeriah; compare 23:19.
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: There were 2,700 capable men among the relatives of Jeriah. King David
        sent them to the east side of the Jordan River and put them in charge of
        the tribes of Reuben and Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh. They were responsible
        for all matters related to God and to the king.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Military Commanders and Divisions'
      title: Military Commanders and Divisions
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the list of Israelite generals and captains,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and their officers, who served the king by supervising the army divisions
        that were on duty each month of the year. Each division served for one month
        and had 24,000 troops.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>commanders of thousands and of hundreds.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jashobeam son of Zabdiel was commander of the first division of 24,000
        troops, which was on duty during the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He was a descendant of Perez and was in charge of all the army officers
        for the first month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Dodai, a descendant of Ahoah, was commander of the second division
        of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the second month. Mikloth was
        his chief officer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Benaiah son of Jehoiada the priest was commander of the third division
        of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the third month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "This was the Benaiah who commanded David\u2019s elite military group
        known as the Thirty. His son Ammizabad was his chief officer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Asahel, the brother of Joab, was commander of the fourth division
        of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the fourth month. Asahel was succeeded
        by his son Zebadiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Shammah[[COMMENT(0)]] the Izrahite was commander of the fifth division
        of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the fifth month.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shamhuth, </b>a variant spelling of Shammah; compare 11:27
          and 2 Sam 23:25.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ira son of Ikkesh from Tekoa was commander of the sixth division
        of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the sixth month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Helez, a descendant of Ephraim from Pelon, was commander of the seventh
        division of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the seventh month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sibbecai, a descendant of Zerah from Hushah, was commander of the
        eighth division of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the eighth month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abiezer from Anathoth in the territory of Benjamin was commander
        of the ninth division of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the ninth
        month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Maharai, a descendant of Zerah from Netophah, was commander of the
        tenth division of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the tenth month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Benaiah from Pirathon in Ephraim was commander of the eleventh division
        of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the eleventh month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Leaders of the Tribes'
      title: Leaders of the Tribes
      number: 15
      content: 'Heled,[[COMMENT(0)]] a descendant of Othniel from Netophah, was commander
        of the twelfth division of 24,000 troops, which was on duty during the twelfth
        month.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Heldai, </b>a variant spelling of Heled; compare 11:30
          and 2 Sam 23:29.
    - name: '16: TribeLeader'
      title: TribeLeader
      number: 16
      content: The following were the tribes of Israel and their leaders:ReubenEliezer
        son of ZicriSimeonShephatiah son of Maacah
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: LeviHashabiah son of KemuelAaron (the priests)Zadok
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: JudahElihu (a brother of David)IssacharOmri son of Michael
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: ZebulunIshmaiah son of ObadiahNaphtaliJeremoth son of Azriel
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: EphraimHoshea son of AzaziahManasseh (west)Joel son of Pedaiah
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Manasseh in Gilead (east)Iddo son of ZechariahBenjaminJaasiel son
        of Abner
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'DanAzarel son of JerohamThese were the leaders of the tribes of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When David took his census, he did not count those who were younger
        than twenty years of age, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had promised
        to make the Israelites as numerous as the stars in heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Officials of David\u2019s Kingdom"
      title: "Officials of David\u2019s Kingdom"
      number: 24
      content: "Joab son of Zeruiah began the census but never finished it because[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the anger of God fell on Israel. The total number was never recorded in King
        David\u2019s official records.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:24 '
        content: Or <b>never finished it, and yet.</b>
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Azmaveth son of Adiel was in charge of the palace treasuries.Jonathan
        son of Uzziah was in charge of the regional treasuries throughout the towns,
        villages, and fortresses of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Ezri son of Kelub was in charge of the field workers who farmed the
        king\u2019s lands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Shimei from Ramah was in charge of the king\u2019s vineyards.Zabdi
        from Shepham was responsible for the grapes and the supplies of wine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Baal-hanan from Geder was in charge of the king\u2019s olive groves
        and sycamore-fig trees in the foothills of Judah.[[COMMENT(0)]]Joash was
        responsible for the supplies of olive oil.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:28 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Shitrai from Sharon was in charge of the cattle on the Sharon Plain.Shaphat
        son of Adlai was responsible for the cattle in the valleys.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Obil the Ishmaelite was in charge of the camels.Jehdeiah from Meronoth
        was in charge of the donkeys.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jaziz the Hagrite was in charge of the king\u2019s flocks of sheep
        and goats.All these officials were overseers of King David\u2019s property.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jonathan, David\u2019s uncle, was a wise counselor to the king, a
        man of great insight, and a scribe. Jehiel the Hacmonite was responsible
        for teaching the king\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Ahithophel was the royal adviser. Hushai the Arkite was the king\u2019s
        friend. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Ahithophel was succeeded by Jehoiada son of Benaiah and by Abiathar.
        Joab was commander of the king\u2019s army."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Instructions to Solomon"
      title: "David\u2019s Instructions to Solomon"
      number: 1
      content: "  David summoned all the officials of Israel to Jerusalem\u2014the
        leaders of the tribes, the commanders of the army divisions, the other generals
        and captains,[[COMMENT(0)]] the overseers of the royal property and livestock,
        the palace officials, the mighty men, and all the other brave warriors in
        the kingdom. "
      comments:
      - number: '28:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David rose to his feet and said: \u201CMy brothers and my people!
        It was my desire to build a Temple where the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant, God\u2019s footstool, could rest permanently. I made the necessary
        preparations for building it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "but God said to me, \u2018You must not build a Temple to honor my
        name, for you are a warrior and have shed much blood.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, has
        chosen me from among all my father\u2019s family to be king over Israel forever.
        For he has chosen the tribe of Judah to rule, and from among the families
        of Judah he chose my father\u2019s family. And from among my father\u2019s
        sons the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was pleased to make me king over all
        Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And from among my sons\u2014for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        given me many\u2014he chose Solomon to succeed me on the throne of Israel
        and to rule over the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s kingdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to me, \u2018Your son Solomon will build my Temple and its
        courtyards, for I have chosen him as my son, and I will be his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And if he continues to obey my commands and regulations as he does
        now, I will make his kingdom last forever.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSo now, with God as our witness, and in the sight of all Israel\u2014the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s assembly\u2014I give you this charge.
        Be careful to obey all the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, so that you may continue to possess this good land and leave it to your
        children as a permanent inheritance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd Solomon, my son, learn to know the God of your ancestors
        intimately. Worship and serve him with your whole heart and a willing mind.
        For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sees every heart and knows every plan
        and thought. If you seek him, you will find him. But if you forsake him,
        he will reject you forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So take this seriously. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen
        you to build a Temple as his sanctuary. Be strong, and do the work.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then David gave Solomon the plans for the Temple and its surroundings,
        including the entry room, the storerooms, the upstairs rooms, the inner rooms,
        and the inner sanctuary\u2014which was the place of atonement. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "David also gave Solomon all the plans he had in mind[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for the courtyards of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple, the
        outside rooms, the treasuries, and the rooms for the gifts dedicated to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '28:12 '
        content: Or <b>the plans of the spirit that was with him.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The king also gave Solomon the instructions concerning the work of
        the various divisions of priests and Levites in the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And he gave specifications for the items in the Temple that were to be used
        for worship.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David gave instructions regarding how much gold and silver should
        be used to make the items needed for service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He told Solomon the amount of gold needed for the gold lampstands
        and lamps, and the amount of silver for the silver lampstands and lamps,
        depending on how each would be used. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He designated the amount of gold for the table on which the Bread
        of the Presence would be placed and the amount of silver for other tables.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'David also designated the amount of gold for the solid gold meat
        hooks used to handle the sacrificial meat and for the basins, pitchers, and
        dishes, as well as the amount of silver for every dish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He designated the amount of refined gold for the altar of incense.
        Finally, he gave him a plan for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s \u201Cchariot\u201D\u2014the
        gold cherubim[[COMMENT(0)]] whose wings were stretched out over the Ark of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Covenant. "
      comments:
      - number: '28:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>for the gold cherub chariot.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CEvery part of this plan,\u201D David told Solomon, \u201Cwas
        given to me in writing from the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>\u201D</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:19 '
        content: Or <b>was written under the direction of the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David continued, \u201CBe strong and courageous, and do the
        work. Don\u2019t be afraid or discouraged, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God, my God, is with you. He will not fail you or forsake you. He will see
        to it that all the work related to the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is finished correctly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The various divisions of priests and Levites will serve in the Temple
        of God. Others with skills of every kind will volunteer, and the officials
        and the entire nation are at your command.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gifts for Building the Temple'
      title: Gifts for Building the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "  Then King David turned to the entire assembly and said, \u201CMy
        son Solomon, whom God has clearly chosen as the next king of Israel, is still
        young and inexperienced. The work ahead of him is enormous, for the Temple
        he will build is not for mere mortals\u2014it is for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God himself! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Using every resource at my command, I have gathered as much as I
        could for building the Temple of my God. Now there is enough gold, silver,
        bronze, iron, and wood, as well as great quantities of onyx, other precious
        stones, costly jewels, and all kinds of fine stone and marble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd now, because of my devotion to the Temple of my God, I
        am giving all of my own private treasures of gold and silver to help in the
        construction. This is in addition to the building materials I have already
        collected for his holy Temple. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I am donating more than 112 tons of gold[[COMMENT(0)]] from Ophir
        and 262 tons of refined silver[[COMMENT(1)]] to be used for overlaying the
        walls of the buildings '
      comments:
      - number: '29:4a '
        content: Hebrew <b>3,000 talents </b>[102 metric tons] <b>of gold.</b>
      - number: '29:4b '
        content: Hebrew <b>7,000 talents </b>[238 metric tons] <b>of silver.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and for the other gold and silver work to be done by the craftsmen.
        Now then, who will follow my example and give offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        today?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the family leaders, the leaders of the tribes of Israel, the
        generals and captains of the army,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the king\u2019s administrative
        officers all gave willingly. "
      comments:
      - number: '29:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the construction of the Temple of God, they gave about 188 tons
        of gold,[[COMMENT(0)]] 10,000 gold coins,[[COMMENT(1)]] 375 tons of silver,[[COMMENT(2)]]
        675 tons of bronze,[[COMMENT(3)]] and 3,750 tons of iron.[[COMMENT(4)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:7a '
        content: Hebrew <b>5,000 talents </b>[170 metric tons] <b>of gold.</b>
      - number: '29:7b '
        content: Hebrew <b>10,000 darics </b>[a Persian coin] <b>of gold, </b>about
          185 pounds or 84 kilograms in weight.
      - number: '29:7c '
        content: Hebrew <b>10,000 talents </b>[340 metric tons] <b>of silver.</b>
      - number: '29:7d '
        content: Hebrew <b>18,000 talents </b>[612 metric tons] <b>of bronze.</b>
      - number: '29:7e '
        content: Hebrew <b>100,000 talents </b>[3,400 metric tons] <b>of iron.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They also contributed numerous precious stones, which were deposited
        in the treasury of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> under the
        care of Jehiel, a descendant of Gershon. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: David\u2019s Prayer of Praise"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer of Praise"
      number: 9
      content: 'The people rejoiced over the offerings, for they had given freely
        and wholeheartedly to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and King David was
        filled with joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David praised the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the presence
        of the whole assembly:\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of our
        ancestor Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]] may you be praised forever and ever! "
      comments:
      - number: '29:10 '
        content: <b>Israel </b>is the name that God gave to Jacob.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yours, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, is the greatness, the power,
        the glory, the victory, and the majesty. Everything in the heavens and on
        earth is yours, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and this is your kingdom.
        We adore you as the one who is over all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Wealth and honor come from you alone, for you rule over everything.
        Power and might are in your hand, and at your discretion people are made
        great and given strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CO our God, we thank you and praise your glorious name! "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But who am I, and who are my people, that we could give anything
        to you? Everything we have has come from you, and we give you only what you
        first gave us! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'We are here for only a moment, visitors and strangers in the land
        as our ancestors were before us. Our days on earth are like a passing shadow,
        gone so soon without a trace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, even this material we
        have gathered to build a Temple to honor your holy name comes from you! It
        all belongs to you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I know, my God, that you examine our hearts and rejoice when you
        find integrity there. You know I have done all this with good motives, and
        I have watched your people offer their gifts willingly and joyously.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of our ancestors Abraham,
        Isaac, and Israel, make your people always want to obey you. See to it that
        their love for you never changes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Give my son Solomon the wholehearted desire to obey all your commands,
        laws, and decrees, and to do everything necessary to build this Temple, for
        which I have made these preparations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Solomon Named as King'
      title: Solomon Named as King
      number: 20
      content: "Then David said to the whole assembly, \u201CGive praise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God!\u201D And the entire assembly praised the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of their ancestors, and they bowed low and knelt before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The next day they brought 1,000 bulls, 1,000 rams, and 1,000 male
        lambs as burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They also brought
        liquid offerings and many other sacrifices on behalf of all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "They feasted and drank in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence with great joy that day.And again they crowned David\u2019s son
        Solomon as their new king. They anointed him before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as their leader, and they anointed Zadok as priest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So Solomon took the throne of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in
        place of his father, David, and he succeeded in everything, and all Israel
        obeyed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All the officials, the warriors, and the sons of King David pledged
        their loyalty to King Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: "25: Summary of David\u2019s Reign"
      title: "Summary of David\u2019s Reign"
      number: 25
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> exalted Solomon in the sight
        of all Israel, and he gave Solomon greater royal splendor than any king in
        Israel before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So David son of Jesse reigned over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He reigned over Israel for forty years, seven of them in Hebron and
        thirty-three in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He died at a ripe old age, having enjoyed long life, wealth, and
        honor. Then his son Solomon ruled in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "All the events of King David\u2019s reign, from beginning to end,
        are written in The Record of Samuel the Seer, The Record of Nathan the Prophet,
        and The Record of Gad the Seer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: These accounts include the mighty deeds of his reign and everything
        that happened to him and to Israel and to all the surrounding kingdoms.
      comments: []
